81// The HashMap for storing continuation pointers.
82// An inline can be split with blocks occuring in between the inline content.
83// When this occurs we need a pointer to the next object. We can basically be
84// split into a sequence of inlines and blocks. The continuation will either be
85// an anonymous block (that houses other blocks) or it will be an inline flow.
86// <b><i><p>Hello</p></i></b>. In this example the <i> will have a block as
87// its continuation but the <b> will just have an inline as its continuation.
88RenderBoxModelObject::ContinuationChainNode::ContinuationChainNode(RenderBoxModelObject& renderer)
89 : renderer(makeWeakPtr(renderer))
90{
91}
92
93RenderBoxModelObject::ContinuationChainNode::~ContinuationChainNode()
94{
95 if (next) {
96 ASSERT(previous);
97 ASSERT(next->previous == this);
98 next->previous = previous;
99 }
100 if (previous) {
101 ASSERT(previous->next == this);
102 previous->next = next;
103 }
104}
105
106void RenderBoxModelObject::ContinuationChainNode::insertAfter(ContinuationChainNode& after)
107{
108 ASSERT(!previous);
109 ASSERT(!next);
110 if ((next = after.next)) {
111 ASSERT(next->previous == &after);
112 next->previous = this;
113 }
114 previous = &after;
115 after.next = this;
116}

134void RenderBoxModelObject::setSelectionState(HighlightState state)
135{
136 if (state == HighlightState::Inside && selectionState() != HighlightState::None)
137 return;
138
139 if ((state == HighlightState::Start && selectionState() == HighlightState::End)
140 || (state == HighlightState::End && selectionState() == HighlightState::Start))
141 RenderLayerModelObject::setSelectionState(HighlightState::Both);
142 else
143 RenderLayerModelObject::setSelectionState(state);
144
145 // FIXME: We should consider whether it is OK propagating to ancestor RenderInlines.
146 // This is a workaround for http://webkit.org/b/32123
147 // The containing block can be null in case of an orphaned tree.
148 RenderBlock* containingBlock = this->containingBlock();
149 if (containingBlock && !containingBlock->isRenderView())
150 containingBlock->setSelectionState(state);
151}

201void RenderBoxModelObject::updateFromStyle()
202{
203 RenderLayerModelObject::updateFromStyle();
204
205 // Set the appropriate bits for a box model object. Since all bits are cleared in styleWillChange,
206 // we only check for bits that could possibly be set to true.
207 const RenderStyle& styleToUse = style();
208 setHasVisibleBoxDecorations(hasVisibleBoxDecorationStyle());
209 setInline(styleToUse.isDisplayInlineType());
210 setPositionState(styleToUse.position());
211 setHorizontalWritingMode(styleToUse.isHorizontalWritingMode());
212 if (styleToUse.isFlippedBlocksWritingMode())
213 view().frameView().setHasFlippedBlockRenderers(true);
214}

216static LayoutSize accumulateInFlowPositionOffsets(const RenderObject* child)
217{
218 if (!child->isAnonymousBlock() || !child->isInFlowPositioned())
219 return LayoutSize();
220 LayoutSize offset;
221 for (RenderElement* parent = downcast<RenderBlock>(*child).inlineContinuation(); is<RenderInline>(parent); parent = parent->parent()) {
222 if (parent->isInFlowPositioned())
223 offset += downcast<RenderInline>(*parent).offsetForInFlowPosition();
224 }
225 return offset;
226}
227
228static inline bool isOutOfFlowPositionedWithImplicitHeight(const RenderBoxModelObject& child)
229{
230 return child.isOutOfFlowPositioned() && !child.style().logicalTop().isAuto() && !child.style().logicalBottom().isAuto();
231}
232
233RenderBlock* RenderBoxModelObject::containingBlockForAutoHeightDetection(Length logicalHeight) const
234{
235 // For percentage heights: The percentage is calculated with respect to the
236 // height of the generated box's containing block. If the height of the
237 // containing block is not specified explicitly (i.e., it depends on content
238 // height), and this element is not absolutely positioned, the used height is
239 // calculated as if 'auto' was specified.
240 if (!logicalHeight.isPercentOrCalculated() || isOutOfFlowPositioned())
241 return nullptr;
242
243 // Anonymous block boxes are ignored when resolving percentage values that
244 // would refer to it: the closest non-anonymous ancestor box is used instead.
245 auto* cb = containingBlock();
246 while (cb && cb->isAnonymous() && !is<RenderView>(cb))
247 cb = cb->containingBlock();
248 if (!cb)
249 return nullptr;
250
251 // Matching RenderBox::percentageLogicalHeightIsResolvable() by
252 // ignoring table cell's attribute value, where it says that table cells
253 // violate what the CSS spec says to do with heights. Basically we don't care
254 // if the cell specified a height or not.
255 if (cb->isTableCell())
256 return nullptr;
257
258 // Match RenderBox::availableLogicalHeightUsing by special casing the layout
259 // view. The available height is taken from the frame.
260 if (cb->isRenderView())
261 return nullptr;
262
263 if (isOutOfFlowPositionedWithImplicitHeight(*cb))
264 return nullptr;
265
266 return cb;
267}
268
269bool RenderBoxModelObject::hasAutoHeightOrContainingBlockWithAutoHeight() const
270{
271 const auto* thisBox = isBox() ? downcast<RenderBox>(this) : nullptr;
272 Length logicalHeightLength = style().logicalHeight();
273 auto* cb = containingBlockForAutoHeightDetection(logicalHeightLength);
274
275 if (logicalHeightLength.isPercentOrCalculated() && cb && isBox())
276 cb->addPercentHeightDescendant(*const_cast<RenderBox*>(downcast<RenderBox>(this)));
277
278 if (thisBox && thisBox->isFlexItem() && downcast<RenderFlexibleBox>(*parent()).useChildOverridingLogicalHeightForPercentageResolution(*thisBox))
279 return false;
280
281 if (thisBox && thisBox->isGridItem() && thisBox->hasOverridingContainingBlockContentLogicalHeight())
282 return thisBox->overridingContainingBlockContentLogicalHeight() == std::nullopt;
283
284 if (logicalHeightLength.isAuto() && !isOutOfFlowPositionedWithImplicitHeight(*this))
285 return true;
286
287 // We need the containing block to have a definite block-size in order to resolve the block-size of the descendant,
288 // except when in quirks mode. Flexboxes follow strict behavior even in quirks mode, though.
289 if (!cb || (document().inQuirksMode() && !cb->isFlexibleBoxIncludingDeprecated()))
290 return false;
291 if (thisBox && thisBox->hasOverridingContainingBlockContentLogicalHeight())
292 return thisBox->overridingContainingBlockContentLogicalHeight() == std::nullopt;
293 return !cb->hasDefiniteLogicalHeight();
294}

296DecodingMode RenderBoxModelObject::decodingModeForImageDraw(const Image& image, const PaintInfo& paintInfo) const
297{
298 if (!is<BitmapImage>(image))
299 return DecodingMode::Synchronous;
300
301 const BitmapImage& bitmapImage = downcast<BitmapImage>(image);
302 if (bitmapImage.canAnimate()) {
303 // The DecodingMode for the current frame has to be Synchronous. The DecodingMode
304 // for the next frame will be calculated in BitmapImage::internalStartAnimation().
305 return DecodingMode::Synchronous;
306 }
307
308 // Large image case.
309#if PLATFORM(IOS_FAMILY)
310 if (IOSApplication::isIBooksStorytime())
311 return DecodingMode::Synchronous;
312#endif
313 if (is<HTMLImageElement>(element())) {
314 auto decodingMode = downcast<HTMLImageElement>(*element()).decodingMode();
315 if (decodingMode != DecodingMode::Auto)
316 return decodingMode;
317 }
318 if (bitmapImage.isLargeImageAsyncDecodingEnabledForTesting())
319 return DecodingMode::Asynchronous;
320 if (document().isImageDocument())
321 return DecodingMode::Synchronous;
322 if (paintInfo.paintBehavior.contains(PaintBehavior::Snapshotting))
323 return DecodingMode::Synchronous;
324 if (!settings().largeImageAsyncDecodingEnabled())
325 return DecodingMode::Synchronous;
326 if (!bitmapImage.canUseAsyncDecodingForLargeImages())
327 return DecodingMode::Synchronous;
328 if (paintInfo.paintBehavior.contains(PaintBehavior::TileFirstPaint))
329 return DecodingMode::Asynchronous;
330 // FIXME: isVisibleInViewport() is not cheap. Find a way to make this condition faster.
331 if (!isVisibleInViewport())
332 return DecodingMode::Asynchronous;
333 return DecodingMode::Synchronous;
334}
335
336LayoutSize RenderBoxModelObject::relativePositionOffset() const
337{
338 // This function has been optimized to avoid calls to containingBlock() in the common case
339 // where all values are either auto or fixed.
340
341 LayoutSize offset = accumulateInFlowPositionOffsets(this);
342
343 // Objects that shrink to avoid floats normally use available line width when computing containing block width. However
344 // in the case of relative positioning using percentages, we can't do this. The offset should always be resolved using the
345 // available width of the containing block. Therefore we don't use containingBlockLogicalWidthForContent() here, but instead explicitly
346 // call availableWidth on our containing block.
347 // However for grid items the containing block is the grid area, so offsets should be resolved against that:
348 // https://drafts.csswg.org/css-grid/#grid-item-sizing
349 if (!style().left().isAuto() || !style().right().isAuto()) {
350 LayoutUnit availableWidth = hasOverridingContainingBlockContentWidth()
351 ? overridingContainingBlockContentWidth().value_or(LayoutUnit()) : containingBlock()->availableWidth();
352 if (!style().left().isAuto()) {
353 if (!style().right().isAuto() && !containingBlock()->style().isLeftToRightDirection())
354 offset.setWidth(-valueForLength(style().right(), !style().right().isFixed() ? availableWidth : 0_lu));
355 else
356 offset.expand(valueForLength(style().left(), !style().left().isFixed() ? availableWidth : 0_lu), 0_lu);
357 } else if (!style().right().isAuto())
358 offset.expand(-valueForLength(style().right(), !style().right().isFixed() ? availableWidth : 0_lu), 0_lu);
359 }
360
361 // If the containing block of a relatively positioned element does not
362 // specify a height, a percentage top or bottom offset should be resolved as
363 // auto. An exception to this is if the containing block has the WinIE quirk
364 // where <html> and <body> assume the size of the viewport. In this case,
365 // calculate the percent offset based on this height.
366 // See <https://bugs.webkit.org/show_bug.cgi?id=26396>.
367 // Another exception is a grid item, as the containing block is the grid area:
368 // https://drafts.csswg.org/css-grid/#grid-item-sizing
369 if (!style().top().isAuto()
370 && (!style().top().isPercentOrCalculated()
371 || !containingBlock()->hasAutoHeightOrContainingBlockWithAutoHeight()
372 || containingBlock()->stretchesToViewport()
373 || hasOverridingContainingBlockContentHeight())) {
374 // FIXME: The computation of the available height is repeated later for "bottom".
375 // We could refactor this and move it to some common code for both ifs, however moving it outside of the ifs
376 // is not possible as it'd cause performance regressions.
377 offset.expand(0_lu, valueForLength(style().top(), !style().top().isFixed()
378 ? (hasOverridingContainingBlockContentHeight() ? overridingContainingBlockContentHeight().value_or(0_lu) : containingBlock()->availableHeight())
379 : LayoutUnit()));
380 } else if (!style().bottom().isAuto()
381 && (!style().bottom().isPercentOrCalculated()
382 || !containingBlock()->hasAutoHeightOrContainingBlockWithAutoHeight()
383 || containingBlock()->stretchesToViewport()
384 || hasOverridingContainingBlockContentHeight())) {
385 // FIXME: Check comment above for "top", it applies here too.
386 offset.expand(0_lu, -valueForLength(style().bottom(), !style().bottom().isFixed()
387 ? (hasOverridingContainingBlockContentHeight() ? overridingContainingBlockContentHeight().value_or(0_lu) : containingBlock()->availableHeight())
388 : LayoutUnit()));
389 }
390
391 return offset;
392}

394LayoutPoint RenderBoxModelObject::adjustedPositionRelativeToOffsetParent(const LayoutPoint& startPoint) const
395{
396 // If the element is the HTML body element or doesn't have a parent
397 // return 0 and stop this algorithm.
398 if (isBody() || !parent())
399 return LayoutPoint();
400
401 LayoutPoint referencePoint = startPoint;
402
403 // If the offsetParent of the element is null, or is the HTML body element,
404 // return the distance between the canvas origin and the left border edge
405 // of the element and stop this algorithm.
406 if (const RenderBoxModelObject* offsetParent = this->offsetParent()) {
407 if (is<RenderBox>(*offsetParent) && !offsetParent->isBody() && !is<RenderTable>(*offsetParent))
408 referencePoint.move(-downcast<RenderBox>(*offsetParent).borderLeft(), -downcast<RenderBox>(*offsetParent).borderTop());
409 if (!isOutOfFlowPositioned() || enclosingFragmentedFlow()) {
410 if (isRelativelyPositioned())
411 referencePoint.move(relativePositionOffset());
412 else if (isStickilyPositioned())
413 referencePoint.move(stickyPositionOffset());
414
415 // CSS regions specification says that region flows should return the body element as their offsetParent.
416 // Since we will bypass the bodys renderer anyway, just end the loop if we encounter a region flow (named flow thread).
417 // See http://dev.w3.org/csswg/css-regions/#cssomview-offset-attributes
418 auto* ancestor = parent();
419 while (ancestor != offsetParent) {
420 // FIXME: What are we supposed to do inside SVG content?
421
422 if (is<RenderMultiColumnFlow>(*ancestor)) {
423 // We need to apply a translation based off what region we are inside.
424 RenderFragmentContainer* fragment = downcast<RenderMultiColumnFlow>(*ancestor).physicalTranslationFromFlowToFragment(referencePoint);
425 if (fragment)
426 referencePoint.moveBy(fragment->topLeftLocation());
427 } else if (!isOutOfFlowPositioned()) {
428 if (is<RenderBox>(*ancestor) && !is<RenderTableRow>(*ancestor))
429 referencePoint.moveBy(downcast<RenderBox>(*ancestor).topLeftLocation());
430 }
431
432 ancestor = ancestor->parent();
433 }
434
435 if (is<RenderBox>(*offsetParent) && offsetParent->isBody() && !offsetParent->isPositioned())
436 referencePoint.moveBy(downcast<RenderBox>(*offsetParent).topLeftLocation());
437 }
438 }
439
440 return referencePoint;
441}

443const RenderBox& RenderBoxModelObject::enclosingClippingBoxForStickyPosition(const RenderLayer** enclosingClippingLayer) const
444{
445 ASSERT(isStickilyPositioned());
446
447 RenderLayer* clipLayer = hasLayer() ? layer()->enclosingOverflowClipLayer(ExcludeSelf) : nullptr;
448
449 if (enclosingClippingLayer)
450 *enclosingClippingLayer = clipLayer;
451
452 return clipLayer ? downcast<RenderBox>(clipLayer->renderer()) : view();
453}
454
455void RenderBoxModelObject::computeStickyPositionConstraints(StickyPositionViewportConstraints& constraints, const FloatRect& constrainingRect) const
456{
457 constraints.setConstrainingRectAtLastLayout(constrainingRect);
458
459 RenderBlock* containingBlock = this->containingBlock();
460 const RenderLayer* enclosingClippingLayer = nullptr;
461 auto& enclosingClippingBox = enclosingClippingBoxForStickyPosition(&enclosingClippingLayer);
462
463 LayoutRect containerContentRect;
464 if (!enclosingClippingLayer || (containingBlock != &enclosingClippingBox))
465 containerContentRect = containingBlock->contentBoxRect();
466 else {
467 containerContentRect = containingBlock->layoutOverflowRect();
468 LayoutPoint containerLocation = containerContentRect.location() + LayoutPoint(containingBlock->borderLeft() + containingBlock->paddingLeft(),
469 containingBlock->borderTop() + containingBlock->paddingTop());
470 containerContentRect.setLocation(containerLocation);
471 }
472
473 LayoutUnit maxWidth = containingBlock->availableLogicalWidth();
474
475 // Sticky positioned element ignore any override logical width on the containing block (as they don't call
476 // containingBlockLogicalWidthForContent). It's unclear whether this is totally fine.
477 LayoutBoxExtent minMargin(minimumValueForLength(style().marginTop(), maxWidth),
478 minimumValueForLength(style().marginRight(), maxWidth),
479 minimumValueForLength(style().marginBottom(), maxWidth),
480 minimumValueForLength(style().marginLeft(), maxWidth));
481
482 // Compute the container-relative area within which the sticky element is allowed to move.
483 containerContentRect.contract(minMargin);
484
485 // Finally compute container rect relative to the scrolling ancestor.
486 FloatRect containerRectRelativeToScrollingAncestor = containingBlock->localToContainerQuad(FloatRect(containerContentRect), &enclosingClippingBox).boundingBox();
487 if (enclosingClippingLayer) {
488 FloatPoint containerLocationRelativeToScrollingAncestor = containerRectRelativeToScrollingAncestor.location() -
489 FloatSize(enclosingClippingBox.borderLeft() + enclosingClippingBox.paddingLeft(),
490 enclosingClippingBox.borderTop() + enclosingClippingBox.paddingTop());
491 if (&enclosingClippingBox != containingBlock) {
492 if (auto* scrollableArea = enclosingClippingLayer->scrollableArea())
493 containerLocationRelativeToScrollingAncestor += scrollableArea->scrollOffset();
494 }
495 containerRectRelativeToScrollingAncestor.setLocation(containerLocationRelativeToScrollingAncestor);
496 }
497 constraints.setContainingBlockRect(containerRectRelativeToScrollingAncestor);
498
499 // Now compute the sticky box rect, also relative to the scrolling ancestor.
500 LayoutRect stickyBoxRect = frameRectForStickyPositioning();
501 LayoutRect flippedStickyBoxRect = stickyBoxRect;
502 containingBlock->flipForWritingMode(flippedStickyBoxRect);
503 FloatRect stickyBoxRelativeToScrollingAnecstor = flippedStickyBoxRect;
504
505 // FIXME: sucks to call localToContainerQuad again, but we can't just offset from the previously computed rect if there are transforms.
506 // Map to the view to avoid including page scale factor.
507 FloatPoint stickyLocationRelativeToScrollingAncestor = flippedStickyBoxRect.location() + containingBlock->localToContainerQuad(FloatRect(FloatPoint(), containingBlock->size()), &enclosingClippingBox).boundingBox().location();
508 if (enclosingClippingLayer) {
509 stickyLocationRelativeToScrollingAncestor -= FloatSize(enclosingClippingBox.borderLeft() + enclosingClippingBox.paddingLeft(),
510 enclosingClippingBox.borderTop() + enclosingClippingBox.paddingTop());
511 if (&enclosingClippingBox != containingBlock) {
512 if (auto* scrollableArea = enclosingClippingLayer->scrollableArea())
513 stickyLocationRelativeToScrollingAncestor += scrollableArea->scrollOffset();
514 }
515 }
516 // FIXME: For now, assume that |this| is not transformed.
517 stickyBoxRelativeToScrollingAnecstor.setLocation(stickyLocationRelativeToScrollingAncestor);
518 constraints.setStickyBoxRect(stickyBoxRelativeToScrollingAnecstor);
519
520 if (!style().left().isAuto()) {
521 constraints.setLeftOffset(valueForLength(style().left(), constrainingRect.width()));
522 constraints.addAnchorEdge(ViewportConstraints::AnchorEdgeLeft);
523 }
524
525 if (!style().right().isAuto()) {
526 constraints.setRightOffset(valueForLength(style().right(), constrainingRect.width()));
527 constraints.addAnchorEdge(ViewportConstraints::AnchorEdgeRight);
528 }
529
530 if (!style().top().isAuto()) {
531 constraints.setTopOffset(valueForLength(style().top(), constrainingRect.height()));
532 constraints.addAnchorEdge(ViewportConstraints::AnchorEdgeTop);
533 }
534
535 if (!style().bottom().isAuto()) {
536 constraints.setBottomOffset(valueForLength(style().bottom(), constrainingRect.height()));
537 constraints.addAnchorEdge(ViewportConstraints::AnchorEdgeBottom);
538 }
539}
540
541FloatRect RenderBoxModelObject::constrainingRectForStickyPosition() const
542{
543 RenderLayer* enclosingClippingLayer = hasLayer() ? layer()->enclosingOverflowClipLayer(ExcludeSelf) : nullptr;
544
545 if (enclosingClippingLayer) {
546 RenderBox& enclosingClippingBox = downcast<RenderBox>(enclosingClippingLayer->renderer());
547 LayoutRect clipRect = enclosingClippingBox.overflowClipRect(LayoutPoint(), nullptr); // FIXME: make this work in regions.
548 clipRect.contract(LayoutSize(enclosingClippingBox.paddingLeft() + enclosingClippingBox.paddingRight(),
549 enclosingClippingBox.paddingTop() + enclosingClippingBox.paddingBottom()));
550
551 FloatRect constrainingRect = enclosingClippingBox.localToContainerQuad(FloatRect(clipRect), &view()).boundingBox();
552
553 auto* scrollableArea = enclosingClippingLayer->scrollableArea();
554 FloatPoint scrollOffset;
555 if (scrollableArea)
556 scrollOffset = FloatPoint() + scrollableArea->scrollOffset();
557
558 float scrollbarOffset = 0;
559 if (enclosingClippingBox.hasLayer() && enclosingClippingBox.shouldPlaceVerticalScrollbarOnLeft() && scrollableArea)
560 scrollbarOffset = scrollableArea->verticalScrollbarWidth(IgnoreOverlayScrollbarSize);
561
562 constrainingRect.setLocation(FloatPoint(scrollOffset.x() + scrollbarOffset, scrollOffset.y()));
563 return constrainingRect;
564 }
565
566 return view().frameView().rectForFixedPositionLayout();
567}
568
569LayoutSize RenderBoxModelObject::stickyPositionOffset() const
570{
571 FloatRect constrainingRect = constrainingRectForStickyPosition();
572 StickyPositionViewportConstraints constraints;
573 computeStickyPositionConstraints(constraints, constrainingRect);
574
575 // The sticky offset is physical, so we can just return the delta computed in absolute coords (though it may be wrong with transforms).
576 return LayoutSize(constraints.computeStickyOffset(constrainingRect));
577}
578
579LayoutSize RenderBoxModelObject::offsetForInFlowPosition() const
580{
581 if (isRelativelyPositioned())
582 return relativePositionOffset();
583
584 if (isStickilyPositioned())
585 return stickyPositionOffset();
586
587 return LayoutSize();
588}

590LayoutUnit RenderBoxModelObject::offsetLeft() const
591{
592 // Note that RenderInline and RenderBox override this to pass a different
593 // startPoint to adjustedPositionRelativeToOffsetParent.
594 return adjustedPositionRelativeToOffsetParent(LayoutPoint()).x();
595}

597LayoutUnit RenderBoxModelObject::offsetTop() const
598{
599 // Note that RenderInline and RenderBox override this to pass a different
600 // startPoint to adjustedPositionRelativeToOffsetParent.
601 return adjustedPositionRelativeToOffsetParent(LayoutPoint()).y();
602}
603
604LayoutUnit RenderBoxModelObject::computedCSSPadding(const Length& padding) const
605{
606 LayoutUnit w;
607 if (padding.isPercentOrCalculated())
608 w = containingBlockLogicalWidthForContent();
609 return minimumValueForLength(padding, w);
610}

612RoundedRect RenderBoxModelObject::getBackgroundRoundedRect(const LayoutRect& borderRect, LegacyInlineFlowBox* box, LayoutUnit inlineBoxWidth, LayoutUnit inlineBoxHeight,
613 bool includeLogicalLeftEdge, bool includeLogicalRightEdge) const
614{
615 RoundedRect border = style().getRoundedBorderFor(borderRect, includeLogicalLeftEdge, includeLogicalRightEdge);
616 if (box && (box->nextLineBox() || box->prevLineBox())) {
617 RoundedRect segmentBorder = style().getRoundedBorderFor(LayoutRect(0_lu, 0_lu, inlineBoxWidth, inlineBoxHeight), includeLogicalLeftEdge, includeLogicalRightEdge);
618 border.setRadii(segmentBorder.radii());
619 }
620 return border;
621}
622
623void RenderBoxModelObject::clipRoundedInnerRect(GraphicsContext& context, const FloatRect& rect, const FloatRoundedRect& clipRect)
624{
625 if (clipRect.isRenderable())
626 context.clipRoundedRect(clipRect);
627 else {
628 // We create a rounded rect for each of the corners and clip it, while making sure we clip opposing corners together.
629 if (!clipRect.radii().topLeft().isEmpty() || !clipRect.radii().bottomRight().isEmpty()) {
630 FloatRect topCorner(clipRect.rect().x(), clipRect.rect().y(), rect.maxX() - clipRect.rect().x(), rect.maxY() - clipRect.rect().y());
631 FloatRoundedRect::Radii topCornerRadii;
632 topCornerRadii.setTopLeft(clipRect.radii().topLeft());
633 context.clipRoundedRect(FloatRoundedRect(topCorner, topCornerRadii));
634
635 FloatRect bottomCorner(rect.x(), rect.y(), clipRect.rect().maxX() - rect.x(), clipRect.rect().maxY() - rect.y());
636 FloatRoundedRect::Radii bottomCornerRadii;
637 bottomCornerRadii.setBottomRight(clipRect.radii().bottomRight());
638 context.clipRoundedRect(FloatRoundedRect(bottomCorner, bottomCornerRadii));
639 }
640
641 if (!clipRect.radii().topRight().isEmpty() || !clipRect.radii().bottomLeft().isEmpty()) {
642 FloatRect topCorner(rect.x(), clipRect.rect().y(), clipRect.rect().maxX() - rect.x(), rect.maxY() - clipRect.rect().y());
643 FloatRoundedRect::Radii topCornerRadii;
644 topCornerRadii.setTopRight(clipRect.radii().topRight());
645 context.clipRoundedRect(FloatRoundedRect(topCorner, topCornerRadii));
646
647 FloatRect bottomCorner(clipRect.rect().x(), rect.y(), rect.maxX() - clipRect.rect().x(), clipRect.rect().maxY() - rect.y());
648 FloatRoundedRect::Radii bottomCornerRadii;
649 bottomCornerRadii.setBottomLeft(clipRect.radii().bottomLeft());
650 context.clipRoundedRect(FloatRoundedRect(bottomCorner, bottomCornerRadii));
651 }
652 }
653}
654
655static LayoutRect shrinkRectByOneDevicePixel(const GraphicsContext& context, const LayoutRect& rect, float devicePixelRatio)
656{
657 LayoutRect shrunkRect = rect;
658 AffineTransform transform = context.getCTM();
659 shrunkRect.inflateX(-ceilToDevicePixel(1_lu / transform.xScale(), devicePixelRatio));
660 shrunkRect.inflateY(-ceilToDevicePixel(1_lu / transform.yScale(), devicePixelRatio));
661 return shrunkRect;
662}
663
664LayoutRect RenderBoxModelObject::borderInnerRectAdjustedForBleedAvoidance(const GraphicsContext& context, const LayoutRect& rect, BackgroundBleedAvoidance bleedAvoidance) const
665{
666 if (bleedAvoidance != BackgroundBleedBackgroundOverBorder)
667 return rect;
668
669 // We shrink the rectangle by one device pixel on each side to make it fully overlap the anti-aliased background border
670 return shrinkRectByOneDevicePixel(context, rect, document().deviceScaleFactor());
671}
672
673RoundedRect RenderBoxModelObject::backgroundRoundedRectAdjustedForBleedAvoidance(const GraphicsContext& context, const LayoutRect& borderRect, BackgroundBleedAvoidance bleedAvoidance, LegacyInlineFlowBox* box, const LayoutSize& boxSize, bool includeLogicalLeftEdge, bool includeLogicalRightEdge) const
674{
675 if (bleedAvoidance == BackgroundBleedShrinkBackground) {
676 // We shrink the rectangle by one device pixel on each side because the bleed is one pixel maximum.
677 return getBackgroundRoundedRect(shrinkRectByOneDevicePixel(context, borderRect, document().deviceScaleFactor()), box, boxSize.width(), boxSize.height(),
678 includeLogicalLeftEdge, includeLogicalRightEdge);
679 }
680 if (bleedAvoidance == BackgroundBleedBackgroundOverBorder)
681 return style().getRoundedInnerBorderFor(borderRect, includeLogicalLeftEdge, includeLogicalRightEdge);
682
683 return getBackgroundRoundedRect(borderRect, box, boxSize.width(), boxSize.height(), includeLogicalLeftEdge, includeLogicalRightEdge);
684}

686static void applyBoxShadowForBackground(GraphicsContext& context, const RenderStyle& style)
687{
688 const ShadowData* boxShadow = style.boxShadow();
689 while (boxShadow->style() != ShadowStyle::Normal)
690 boxShadow = boxShadow->next();
691
692 FloatSize shadowOffset(boxShadow->x(), boxShadow->y());
693 context.setShadow(shadowOffset, boxShadow->radius(), style.colorByApplyingColorFilter(boxShadow->color()), boxShadow->isWebkitBoxShadow() ? ShadowRadiusMode::Legacy : ShadowRadiusMode::Default);
694}

697{
698 return view().imageQualityController().chooseInterpolationQuality(context, this, image, layer, size);
699}

701void RenderBoxModelObject::paintMaskForTextFillBox(ImageBuffer* maskImage, const FloatRect& maskRect, LegacyInlineFlowBox* box, const LayoutRect& scrolledPaintRect)
702{
703 GraphicsContext& maskImageContext = maskImage->context();
704 maskImageContext.translate(-maskRect.location());
705
706 // Now add the text to the clip. We do this by painting using a special paint phase that signals to
707 // LegacyInlineTextBoxes that they should just add their contents to the clip.
708 PaintInfo info(maskImageContext, LayoutRect { maskRect }, PaintPhase::TextClip, PaintBehavior::ForceBlackText);
709 if (box) {
710 const LegacyRootInlineBox& rootBox = box->root();
711 box->paint(info, LayoutPoint(scrolledPaintRect.x() - box->x(), scrolledPaintRect.y() - box->y()), rootBox.lineTop(), rootBox.lineBottom());
712 } else {
713 LayoutSize localOffset = is<RenderBox>(*this) ? downcast<RenderBox>(*this).locationOffset() : LayoutSize();
714 paint(info, scrolledPaintRect.location() - localOffset);
715 }
716}
717
718void RenderBoxModelObject::paintFillLayerExtended(const PaintInfo& paintInfo, const Color& color, const FillLayer& bgLayer, const LayoutRect& rect,
719 BackgroundBleedAvoidance bleedAvoidance, LegacyInlineFlowBox* box, const LayoutSize& boxSize, CompositeOperator op, RenderElement* backgroundObject, BaseBackgroundColorUsage baseBgColorUsage)
720{
721 GraphicsContext& context = paintInfo.context();
722
723 if ((context.paintingDisabled() && !context.detectingContentfulPaint()) || rect.isEmpty())
724 return;
725
726 bool includeLeftEdge = box ? box->includeLogicalLeftEdge() : true;
727 bool includeRightEdge = box ? box->includeLogicalRightEdge() : true;
728
729 bool hasRoundedBorder = style().hasBorderRadius() && (includeLeftEdge || includeRightEdge);
730 bool clippedWithLocalScrolling = hasOverflowClip() && bgLayer.attachment() == FillAttachment::LocalBackground;
731 bool isBorderFill = bgLayer.clip() == FillBox::Border;
732 bool isRoot = this->isDocumentElementRenderer();
733
734 Color bgColor = color;
735 StyleImage* bgImage = bgLayer.image();
736 bool shouldPaintBackgroundImage = bgImage && bgImage->canRender(this, style().effectiveZoom());
737
738 if (context.detectingContentfulPaint()) {
739 if (!context.contenfulPaintDetected() && shouldPaintBackgroundImage && bgImage->cachedImage()) {
740 if (style().backgroundSizeType() != FillSizeType::Size || !style().backgroundSizeLength().isEmpty())
741 context.setContentfulPaintDetected();
742 return;
743 }
744 }
745
746 if (context.invalidatingImagesWithAsyncDecodes()) {
747 if (shouldPaintBackgroundImage && bgImage->cachedImage()->isClientWaitingForAsyncDecoding(*this))
748 bgImage->cachedImage()->removeAllClientsWaitingForAsyncDecoding();
749 return;
750 }
751
752 bool forceBackgroundToWhite = false;
753 if (document().printing()) {
754 if (style().printColorAdjust() == PrintColorAdjust::Economy)
755 forceBackgroundToWhite = true;
756 if (settings().shouldPrintBackgrounds())
757 forceBackgroundToWhite = false;
758 }
759
760 // When printing backgrounds is disabled or using economy mode,
761 // change existing background colors and images to a solid white background.
762 // If there's no bg color or image, leave it untouched to avoid affecting transparency.
763 // We don't try to avoid loading the background images, because this style flag is only set
764 // when printing, and at that point we've already loaded the background images anyway. (To avoid
765 // loading the background images we'd have to do this check when applying styles rather than
766 // while rendering.)
767 if (forceBackgroundToWhite) {
768 // Note that we can't reuse this variable below because the bgColor might be changed
769 bool shouldPaintBackgroundColor = !bgLayer.next() && bgColor.isVisible();
770 if (shouldPaintBackgroundImage || shouldPaintBackgroundColor) {
771 bgColor = Color::white;
772 shouldPaintBackgroundImage = false;
773 }
774 }
775
776 bool baseBgColorOnly = (baseBgColorUsage == BaseBackgroundColorOnly);
777 if (baseBgColorOnly && (!isRoot || bgLayer.next() || bgColor.isOpaque()))
778 return;
779
780 bool colorVisible = bgColor.isVisible();
781 float deviceScaleFactor = document().deviceScaleFactor();
782 FloatRect pixelSnappedRect = snapRectToDevicePixels(rect, deviceScaleFactor);
783
784 // Fast path for drawing simple color backgrounds.
785 if (!isRoot && !clippedWithLocalScrolling && !shouldPaintBackgroundImage && isBorderFill && !bgLayer.next()) {
786 if (!colorVisible)
787 return;
788
789 bool boxShadowShouldBeAppliedToBackground = this->boxShadowShouldBeAppliedToBackground(rect.location(), bleedAvoidance, box);
790 GraphicsContextStateSaver shadowStateSaver(context, boxShadowShouldBeAppliedToBackground);
791 if (boxShadowShouldBeAppliedToBackground)
792 applyBoxShadowForBackground(context, style());
793
794 if (hasRoundedBorder && bleedAvoidance != BackgroundBleedUseTransparencyLayer) {
795 FloatRoundedRect pixelSnappedBorder = backgroundRoundedRectAdjustedForBleedAvoidance(context, rect, bleedAvoidance, box, boxSize,
796 includeLeftEdge, includeRightEdge).pixelSnappedRoundedRectForPainting(deviceScaleFactor);
797 if (pixelSnappedBorder.isRenderable()) {
798 CompositeOperator previousOperator = context.compositeOperation();
799 bool saveRestoreCompositeOp = op != previousOperator;
800 if (saveRestoreCompositeOp)
801 context.setCompositeOperation(op);
802
803 context.fillRoundedRect(pixelSnappedBorder, bgColor);
804
805 if (saveRestoreCompositeOp)
806 context.setCompositeOperation(previousOperator);
807 } else {
808 context.save();
809 clipRoundedInnerRect(context, pixelSnappedRect, pixelSnappedBorder);
810 context.fillRect(pixelSnappedBorder.rect(), bgColor, op);
811 context.restore();
812 }
813 } else
814 context.fillRect(pixelSnappedRect, bgColor, op);
815
816 return;
817 }
818
819 // FillBox::Border radius clipping is taken care of by BackgroundBleedUseTransparencyLayer
820 bool clipToBorderRadius = hasRoundedBorder && !(isBorderFill && bleedAvoidance == BackgroundBleedUseTransparencyLayer);
821 GraphicsContextStateSaver clipToBorderStateSaver(context, clipToBorderRadius);
822 if (clipToBorderRadius) {
823 RoundedRect border = isBorderFill ? backgroundRoundedRectAdjustedForBleedAvoidance(context, rect, bleedAvoidance, box, boxSize, includeLeftEdge, includeRightEdge) : getBackgroundRoundedRect(rect, box, boxSize.width(), boxSize.height(), includeLeftEdge, includeRightEdge);
824
825 // Clip to the padding or content boxes as necessary.
826 if (bgLayer.clip() == FillBox::Content) {
827 border = style().getRoundedInnerBorderFor(border.rect(),
828 paddingTop() + borderTop(), paddingBottom() + borderBottom(), paddingLeft() + borderLeft(), paddingRight() + borderRight(), includeLeftEdge, includeRightEdge);
829 } else if (bgLayer.clip() == FillBox::Padding)
830 border = style().getRoundedInnerBorderFor(border.rect(), includeLeftEdge, includeRightEdge);
831
832 clipRoundedInnerRect(context, pixelSnappedRect, border.pixelSnappedRoundedRectForPainting(deviceScaleFactor));
833 }
834
835 LayoutUnit bLeft = includeLeftEdge ? borderLeft() : 0_lu;
836 LayoutUnit bRight = includeRightEdge ? borderRight() : 0_lu;
837 LayoutUnit pLeft = includeLeftEdge ? paddingLeft() : 0_lu;
838 LayoutUnit pRight = includeRightEdge ? paddingRight() : 0_lu;
839
840 GraphicsContextStateSaver clipWithScrollingStateSaver(context, clippedWithLocalScrolling);
841 LayoutRect scrolledPaintRect = rect;
842 if (clippedWithLocalScrolling) {
843 // Clip to the overflow area.
844 auto& thisBox = downcast<RenderBox>(*this);
845 context.clip(thisBox.overflowClipRect(rect.location()));
846
847 // Adjust the paint rect to reflect a scrolled content box with borders at the ends.
848 scrolledPaintRect.moveBy(-thisBox.scrollPosition());
849 scrolledPaintRect.setWidth(bLeft + layer()->scrollWidth() + bRight);
850 scrolledPaintRect.setHeight(borderTop() + layer()->scrollHeight() + borderBottom());
851 }
852
853 GraphicsContextStateSaver backgroundClipStateSaver(context, false);
854 RefPtr<ImageBuffer> maskImage;
855 FloatRect maskRect;
856
857 if (bgLayer.clip() == FillBox::Padding || bgLayer.clip() == FillBox::Content) {
858 // Clip to the padding or content boxes as necessary.
859 if (!clipToBorderRadius) {
860 bool includePadding = bgLayer.clip() == FillBox::Content;
861 LayoutRect clipRect = LayoutRect(scrolledPaintRect.x() + bLeft + (includePadding ? pLeft : 0_lu),
862 scrolledPaintRect.y() + borderTop() + (includePadding ? paddingTop() : 0_lu),
863 scrolledPaintRect.width() - bLeft - bRight - (includePadding ? pLeft + pRight : 0_lu),
864 scrolledPaintRect.height() - borderTop() - borderBottom() - (includePadding ? paddingTop() + paddingBottom() : 0_lu));
865 backgroundClipStateSaver.save();
866 context.clip(clipRect);
867 }
868 } else if (bgLayer.clip() == FillBox::Text) {
869 // We have to draw our text into a mask that can then be used to clip background drawing.
870 // First figure out how big the mask has to be. It should be no bigger than what we need
871 // to actually render, so we should intersect the dirty rect with the border box of the background.
872 maskRect = snapRectToDevicePixels(rect, deviceScaleFactor);
873 maskRect.intersect(snapRectToDevicePixels(paintInfo.rect, deviceScaleFactor));
874
875 // Now create the mask.
876 maskImage = ImageBuffer::createCompatibleBuffer(maskRect.size(), DestinationColorSpace::SRGB(), context);
877 if (!maskImage)
878 return;
879 paintMaskForTextFillBox(maskImage.get(), maskRect, box, scrolledPaintRect);
880
881 // The mask has been created. Now we just need to clip to it.
882 backgroundClipStateSaver.save();
883 context.clip(maskRect);
884 context.beginTransparencyLayer(1);
885 }
886
887 // Only fill with a base color (e.g., white) if we're the root document, since iframes/frames with
888 // no background in the child document should show the parent's background.
889 bool isOpaqueRoot = false;
890 if (isRoot) {
891 isOpaqueRoot = true;
892 if (!bgLayer.next() && !bgColor.isOpaque()) {
893 HTMLFrameOwnerElement* ownerElement = document().ownerElement();
894 if (ownerElement) {
895 if (!ownerElement->hasTagName(frameTag)) {
896 // Locate the <body> element using the DOM. This is easier than trying
897 // to crawl around a render tree with potential :before/:after content and
898 // anonymous blocks created by inline <body> tags etc. We can locate the <body>
899 // render object very easily via the DOM.
900 if (HTMLElement* body = document().bodyOrFrameset()) {
901 // Can't scroll a frameset document anyway.
902 isOpaqueRoot = is<HTMLFrameSetElement>(*body);
903 } else {
904 // SVG documents and XML documents with SVG root nodes are transparent.
905 isOpaqueRoot = !document().hasSVGRootNode();
906 }
907 }
908 } else
909 isOpaqueRoot = !view().frameView().isTransparent();
910 }
911 view().frameView().setContentIsOpaque(isOpaqueRoot);
912 }
913
914 // Paint the color first underneath all images, culled if background image occludes it.
915 // FIXME: In the bgLayer.hasFiniteBounds() case, we could improve the culling test
916 // by verifying whether the background image covers the entire layout rect.
917 if (!bgLayer.next()) {
918 LayoutRect backgroundRect(scrolledPaintRect);
919 bool boxShadowShouldBeAppliedToBackground = this->boxShadowShouldBeAppliedToBackground(rect.location(), bleedAvoidance, box);
920 if (boxShadowShouldBeAppliedToBackground || !shouldPaintBackgroundImage || !bgLayer.hasOpaqueImage(*this) || !bgLayer.hasRepeatXY() || bgLayer.isEmpty()) {
921 if (!boxShadowShouldBeAppliedToBackground)
922 backgroundRect.intersect(paintInfo.rect);
923
924 // If we have an alpha and we are painting the root element, blend with the base background color.
925 Color baseColor;
926 bool shouldClearBackground = false;
927 if ((baseBgColorUsage != BaseBackgroundColorSkip) && isOpaqueRoot) {
928 baseColor = view().frameView().baseBackgroundColor();
929 if (!baseColor.isVisible())
930 shouldClearBackground = true;
931 }
932
933 GraphicsContextStateSaver shadowStateSaver(context, boxShadowShouldBeAppliedToBackground);
934 if (boxShadowShouldBeAppliedToBackground)
935 applyBoxShadowForBackground(context, style());
936
937 FloatRect backgroundRectForPainting = snapRectToDevicePixels(backgroundRect, deviceScaleFactor);
938 if (baseColor.isVisible()) {
939 if (!baseBgColorOnly && bgColor.isVisible())
940 baseColor = blendSourceOver(baseColor, bgColor);
941 context.fillRect(backgroundRectForPainting, baseColor, CompositeOperator::Copy);
942 } else if (!baseBgColorOnly && bgColor.isVisible()) {
943 auto operation = context.compositeOperation();
944 if (shouldClearBackground) {
945 if (op == CompositeOperator::DestinationOut) // We're punching out the background.
946 operation = op;
947 else
948 operation = CompositeOperator::Copy;
949 }
950 context.fillRect(backgroundRectForPainting, bgColor, operation);
951 } else if (shouldClearBackground)
952 context.clearRect(backgroundRectForPainting);
953 }
954 }
955
956 // no progressive loading of the background image
957 if (!baseBgColorOnly && shouldPaintBackgroundImage) {
958 auto geometry = calculateBackgroundImageGeometry(paintInfo.paintContainer, bgLayer, rect.location(), scrolledPaintRect, backgroundObject);
959 geometry.clip(LayoutRect(pixelSnappedRect));
960 RefPtr<Image> image;
961 if (!geometry.destRect().isEmpty() && (image = bgImage->image(backgroundObject ? backgroundObject : this, geometry.tileSize()))) {
962 context.setDrawLuminanceMask(bgLayer.maskSourceType() == MaskSourceType::Luminance);
963
964 if (is<BitmapImage>(image))
965 downcast<BitmapImage>(*image).updateFromSettings(settings());
966
967 ImagePaintingOptions options = {
968 op == CompositeOperator::SourceOver ? bgLayer.composite() : op,
969 bgLayer.blendMode(),
970 decodingModeForImageDraw(*image, paintInfo),
971 ImageOrientation::FromImage,
972 chooseInterpolationQuality(context, *image, &bgLayer, geometry.tileSize())
973 };
974
975 auto drawResult = context.drawTiledImage(*image, geometry.destRect(), toLayoutPoint(geometry.relativePhase()), geometry.tileSize(), geometry.spaceSize(), options);
976 if (drawResult == ImageDrawResult::DidRequestDecoding) {
977 ASSERT(bgImage->hasCachedImage());
978 bgImage->cachedImage()->addClientWaitingForAsyncDecoding(*this);
979 }
980 }
981 }
982
983 if (maskImage && bgLayer.clip() == FillBox::Text) {
984 context.drawConsumingImageBuffer(WTFMove(maskImage), maskRect, CompositeOperator::DestinationIn);
985 context.endTransparencyLayer();
986 }
987}
988
989static inline LayoutUnit resolveWidthForRatio(LayoutUnit height, const LayoutSize& intrinsicRatio)
990{
991 return height * intrinsicRatio.width() / intrinsicRatio.height();
992}
993
994static inline LayoutUnit resolveHeightForRatio(LayoutUnit width, const LayoutSize& intrinsicRatio)
995{
996 return width * intrinsicRatio.height() / intrinsicRatio.width();
997}
998
999static inline LayoutSize resolveAgainstIntrinsicWidthOrHeightAndRatio(const LayoutSize& size, const LayoutSize& intrinsicRatio, LayoutUnit useWidth, LayoutUnit useHeight)
1000{
1001 if (intrinsicRatio.isEmpty()) {
1002 if (useWidth)
1003 return LayoutSize(useWidth, size.height());
1004 return LayoutSize(size.width(), useHeight);
1005 }
1006
1007 if (useWidth)
1008 return LayoutSize(useWidth, resolveHeightForRatio(useWidth, intrinsicRatio));
1009 return LayoutSize(resolveWidthForRatio(useHeight, intrinsicRatio), useHeight);
1010}
1011
1012static inline LayoutSize resolveAgainstIntrinsicRatio(const LayoutSize& size, const LayoutSize& intrinsicRatio)
1013{
1014 // Two possible solutions: (size.width(), solutionHeight) or (solutionWidth, size.height())
1015 // "... must be assumed to be the largest dimensions..." = easiest answer: the rect with the largest surface area.
1016
1017 LayoutUnit solutionWidth = resolveWidthForRatio(size.height(), intrinsicRatio);
1018 LayoutUnit solutionHeight = resolveHeightForRatio(size.width(), intrinsicRatio);
1019 if (solutionWidth <= size.width()) {
1020 if (solutionHeight <= size.height()) {
1021 // If both solutions fit, choose the one covering the larger area.
1022 LayoutUnit areaOne = solutionWidth * size.height();
1023 LayoutUnit areaTwo = size.width() * solutionHeight;
1024 if (areaOne < areaTwo)
1025 return LayoutSize(size.width(), solutionHeight);
1026 return LayoutSize(solutionWidth, size.height());
1027 }
1028
1029 // Only the first solution fits.
1030 return LayoutSize(solutionWidth, size.height());
1031 }
1032
1033 // Only the second solution fits, assert that.
1034 ASSERT(solutionHeight <= size.height());
1035 return LayoutSize(size.width(), solutionHeight);
1036}
1037
1038LayoutSize RenderBoxModelObject::calculateImageIntrinsicDimensions(StyleImage* image, const LayoutSize& positioningAreaSize, ScaleByEffectiveZoomOrNot shouldScaleOrNot) const
1039{
1040 // A generated image without a fixed size, will always return the container size as intrinsic size.
1041 if (image->isGeneratedImage() && image->usesImageContainerSize())
1042 return LayoutSize(positioningAreaSize.width(), positioningAreaSize.height());
1043
1044 Length intrinsicWidth;
1045 Length intrinsicHeight;
1046 FloatSize intrinsicRatio;
1047 image->computeIntrinsicDimensions(this, intrinsicWidth, intrinsicHeight, intrinsicRatio);
1048
1049 ASSERT(!intrinsicWidth.isPercentOrCalculated());
1050 ASSERT(!intrinsicHeight.isPercentOrCalculated());
1051
1052 LayoutSize resolvedSize(intrinsicWidth.value(), intrinsicHeight.value());
1053 LayoutSize minimumSize(resolvedSize.width() > 0 ? 1 : 0, resolvedSize.height() > 0 ? 1 : 0);
1054
1055 if (shouldScaleOrNot == ScaleByEffectiveZoom)
1056 resolvedSize.scale(style().effectiveZoom());
1057 resolvedSize.clampToMinimumSize(minimumSize);
1058
1059 if (!resolvedSize.isEmpty())
1060 return resolvedSize;
1061
1062 // If the image has one of either an intrinsic width or an intrinsic height:
1063 // * and an intrinsic aspect ratio, then the missing dimension is calculated from the given dimension and the ratio.
1064 // * and no intrinsic aspect ratio, then the missing dimension is assumed to be the size of the rectangle that
1065 // establishes the coordinate system for the 'background-position' property.
1066 if (resolvedSize.width() > 0 || resolvedSize.height() > 0)
1067 return resolveAgainstIntrinsicWidthOrHeightAndRatio(positioningAreaSize, LayoutSize(intrinsicRatio), resolvedSize.width(), resolvedSize.height());
1068
1069 // If the image has no intrinsic dimensions and has an intrinsic ratio the dimensions must be assumed to be the
1070 // largest dimensions at that ratio such that neither dimension exceeds the dimensions of the rectangle that
1071 // establishes the coordinate system for the 'background-position' property.
1072 if (!intrinsicRatio.isEmpty())
1073 return resolveAgainstIntrinsicRatio(positioningAreaSize, LayoutSize(intrinsicRatio));
1074
1075 // If the image has no intrinsic ratio either, then the dimensions must be assumed to be the rectangle that
1076 // establishes the coordinate system for the 'background-position' property.
1077 return positioningAreaSize;
1078}
1079
1080LayoutSize RenderBoxModelObject::calculateFillTileSize(const FillLayer& fillLayer, const LayoutSize& positioningAreaSize) const
1081{
1082 StyleImage* image = fillLayer.image();
1083 FillSizeType type = fillLayer.size().type;
1084 auto devicePixelSize = LayoutUnit { 1.0 / document().deviceScaleFactor() };
1085
1086 LayoutSize imageIntrinsicSize;
1087 if (image) {
1088 imageIntrinsicSize = calculateImageIntrinsicDimensions(image, positioningAreaSize, ScaleByEffectiveZoom);
1089 imageIntrinsicSize.scale(1 / image->imageScaleFactor(), 1 / image->imageScaleFactor());
1090 } else
1091 imageIntrinsicSize = positioningAreaSize;
1092
1093 switch (type) {
1094 case FillSizeType::Size: {
1095 LayoutSize tileSize = positioningAreaSize;
1096
1097 Length layerWidth = fillLayer.size().size.width;
1098 Length layerHeight = fillLayer.size().size.height;
1099
1100 if (layerWidth.isFixed())
1101 tileSize.setWidth(layerWidth.value());
1102 else if (layerWidth.isPercentOrCalculated()) {
1103 auto resolvedWidth = valueForLength(layerWidth, positioningAreaSize.width());
1104 // Non-zero resolved value should always produce some content.
1105 tileSize.setWidth(!resolvedWidth ? resolvedWidth : std::max(devicePixelSize, resolvedWidth));
1106 }
1107
1108 if (layerHeight.isFixed())
1109 tileSize.setHeight(layerHeight.value());
1110 else if (layerHeight.isPercentOrCalculated()) {
1111 auto resolvedHeight = valueForLength(layerHeight, positioningAreaSize.height());
1112 // Non-zero resolved value should always produce some content.
1113 tileSize.setHeight(!resolvedHeight ? resolvedHeight : std::max(devicePixelSize, resolvedHeight));
1114 }
1115
1116 // If one of the values is auto we have to use the appropriate
1117 // scale to maintain our aspect ratio.
1118 if (layerWidth.isAuto() && !layerHeight.isAuto()) {
1119 if (imageIntrinsicSize.height())
1120 tileSize.setWidth(imageIntrinsicSize.width() * tileSize.height() / imageIntrinsicSize.height());
1121 } else if (!layerWidth.isAuto() && layerHeight.isAuto()) {
1122 if (imageIntrinsicSize.width())
1123 tileSize.setHeight(imageIntrinsicSize.height() * tileSize.width() / imageIntrinsicSize.width());
1124 } else if (layerWidth.isAuto() && layerHeight.isAuto()) {
1125 // If both width and height are auto, use the image's intrinsic size.
1126 tileSize = imageIntrinsicSize;
1127 }
1128
1129 tileSize.clampNegativeToZero();
1130 return tileSize;
1131 }
1132 case FillSizeType::None: {
1133 // If both values are auto then the intrinsic width and/or height of the image should be used, if any.
1134 if (!imageIntrinsicSize.isEmpty())
1135 return imageIntrinsicSize;
1136
1137 // If the image has neither an intrinsic width nor an intrinsic height, its size is determined as for contain.
1138 type = FillSizeType::Contain;
1139 }
1140 FALLTHROUGH;
1141 case FillSizeType::Contain:
1142 case FillSizeType::Cover: {
1143 // Scale computation needs higher precision than what LayoutUnit can offer.
1144 FloatSize localImageIntrinsicSize = imageIntrinsicSize;
1145 FloatSize localPositioningAreaSize = positioningAreaSize;
1146
1147 float horizontalScaleFactor = localImageIntrinsicSize.width() ? (localPositioningAreaSize.width() / localImageIntrinsicSize.width()) : 1;
1148 float verticalScaleFactor = localImageIntrinsicSize.height() ? (localPositioningAreaSize.height() / localImageIntrinsicSize.height()) : 1;
1149 float scaleFactor = type == FillSizeType::Contain ? std::min(horizontalScaleFactor, verticalScaleFactor) : std::max(horizontalScaleFactor, verticalScaleFactor);
1150
1151 if (localImageIntrinsicSize.isEmpty())
1152 return { };
1153
1154 return LayoutSize(localImageIntrinsicSize.scaled(scaleFactor).expandedTo({ devicePixelSize, devicePixelSize }));
1155 }
1156 }
1157
1158 ASSERT_NOT_REACHED();
1159 return { };
1160}
1161
1162static void pixelSnapBackgroundImageGeometryForPainting(LayoutRect& destinationRect, LayoutSize& tileSize, LayoutSize& phase, LayoutSize& space, float scaleFactor)
1163{
1164 tileSize = LayoutSize(snapRectToDevicePixels(LayoutRect(destinationRect.location(), tileSize), scaleFactor).size());
1165 phase = LayoutSize(snapRectToDevicePixels(LayoutRect(destinationRect.location(), phase), scaleFactor).size());
1166 space = LayoutSize(snapRectToDevicePixels(LayoutRect(LayoutPoint(), space), scaleFactor).size());
1167 destinationRect = LayoutRect(snapRectToDevicePixels(destinationRect, scaleFactor));
1168}
1169
1170bool RenderBoxModelObject::fixedBackgroundPaintsInLocalCoordinates() const
1171{
1172 if (!isDocumentElementRenderer())
1173 return false;
1174
1175 if (view().frameView().paintBehavior().contains(PaintBehavior::FlattenCompositingLayers))
1176 return false;
1177
1178 RenderLayer* rootLayer = view().layer();
1179 if (!rootLayer || !rootLayer->isComposited())
1180 return false;
1181
1182 return rootLayer->backing()->backgroundLayerPaintsFixedRootBackground();
1183}
1184
1185static inline LayoutUnit getSpace(LayoutUnit areaSize, LayoutUnit tileSize)
1186{
1187 int numberOfTiles = areaSize / tileSize;
1188 LayoutUnit space = -1;
1189
1190 if (numberOfTiles > 1)
1191 space = (areaSize - numberOfTiles * tileSize) / (numberOfTiles - 1);
1192
1193 return space;
1194}
1195
1196static LayoutUnit resolveEdgeRelativeLength(const Length& length, Edge edge, LayoutUnit availableSpace, const LayoutSize& areaSize, const LayoutSize& tileSize)
1197{
1198 LayoutUnit result = minimumValueForLength(length, availableSpace);
1199
1200 if (edge == Edge::Right)
1201 return areaSize.width() - tileSize.width() - result;
1202
1203 if (edge == Edge::Bottom)
1204 return areaSize.height() - tileSize.height() - result;
1205
1206 return result;
1207}
1208
1209BackgroundImageGeometry RenderBoxModelObject::calculateBackgroundImageGeometry(const RenderLayerModelObject* paintContainer, const FillLayer& fillLayer, const LayoutPoint& paintOffset,
1210 const LayoutRect& borderBoxRect, RenderElement* backgroundObject) const
1211{
1212 LayoutUnit left;
1213 LayoutUnit top;
1214 LayoutSize positioningAreaSize;
1215 // Determine the background positioning area and set destination rect to the background painting area.
1216 // Destination rect will be adjusted later if the background is non-repeating.
1217 // FIXME: transforms spec says that fixed backgrounds behave like scroll inside transforms. https://bugs.webkit.org/show_bug.cgi?id=15679
1218 LayoutRect destinationRect(borderBoxRect);
1219 bool fixedAttachment = fillLayer.attachment() == FillAttachment::FixedBackground;
1220 float deviceScaleFactor = document().deviceScaleFactor();
1221 if (!fixedAttachment) {
1222 LayoutUnit right;
1223 LayoutUnit bottom;
1224 // Scroll and Local.
1225 if (fillLayer.origin() != FillBox::Border) {
1226 left = borderLeft();
1227 right = borderRight();
1228 top = borderTop();
1229 bottom = borderBottom();
1230 if (fillLayer.origin() == FillBox::Content) {
1231 left += paddingLeft();
1232 right += paddingRight();
1233 top += paddingTop();
1234 bottom += paddingBottom();
1235 }
1236 }
1237
1238 // The background of the box generated by the root element covers the entire canvas including
1239 // its margins. Since those were added in already, we have to factor them out when computing
1240 // the background positioning area.
1241 if (isDocumentElementRenderer()) {
1242 positioningAreaSize = downcast<RenderBox>(*this).size() - LayoutSize(left + right, top + bottom);
1243 positioningAreaSize = LayoutSize(snapSizeToDevicePixel(positioningAreaSize, LayoutPoint(), deviceScaleFactor));
1244 if (view().frameView().hasExtendedBackgroundRectForPainting()) {
1245 LayoutRect extendedBackgroundRect = view().frameView().extendedBackgroundRectForPainting();
1246 left += (marginLeft() - extendedBackgroundRect.x());
1247 top += (marginTop() - extendedBackgroundRect.y());
1248 }
1249 } else {
1250 positioningAreaSize = borderBoxRect.size() - LayoutSize(left + right, top + bottom);
1251 positioningAreaSize = LayoutSize(snapRectToDevicePixels(LayoutRect(paintOffset, positioningAreaSize), deviceScaleFactor).size());
1252 }
1253 } else {
1254 LayoutRect viewportRect;
1255 float topContentInset = 0;
1256 if (settings().fixedBackgroundsPaintRelativeToDocument())
1257 viewportRect = view().unscaledDocumentRect();
1258 else {
1259 FrameView& frameView = view().frameView();
1260 bool useFixedLayout = frameView.useFixedLayout() && !frameView.fixedLayoutSize().isEmpty();
1261
1262 if (useFixedLayout) {
1263 // Use the fixedLayoutSize() when useFixedLayout() because the rendering will scale
1264 // down the frameView to to fit in the current viewport.
1265 viewportRect.setSize(frameView.fixedLayoutSize());
1266 } else
1267 viewportRect.setSize(frameView.sizeForVisibleContent());
1268
1269 if (fixedBackgroundPaintsInLocalCoordinates()) {
1270 if (!useFixedLayout) {
1271 // Shifting location up by topContentInset is needed for layout tests which expect
1272 // layout to be shifted down when calling window.internals.setTopContentInset().
1273 topContentInset = frameView.topContentInset(ScrollView::TopContentInsetType::WebCoreOrPlatformContentInset);
1274 viewportRect.setLocation(LayoutPoint(0, -topContentInset));
1275 }
1276 } else if (useFixedLayout || frameView.frameScaleFactor() != 1) {
1277 // scrollPositionForFixedPosition() is adjusted for page scale and it does not include
1278 // topContentInset so do not add it to the calculation below.
1279 viewportRect.setLocation(frameView.scrollPositionForFixedPosition());
1280 } else {
1281 // documentScrollPositionRelativeToViewOrigin() includes -topContentInset in its height
1282 // so we need to account for that in calculating the phase size
1283 topContentInset = frameView.topContentInset(ScrollView::TopContentInsetType::WebCoreOrPlatformContentInset);
1284 viewportRect.setLocation(frameView.documentScrollPositionRelativeToViewOrigin());
1285 }
1286
1287 top += topContentInset;
1288 }
1289
1290 if (paintContainer)
1291 viewportRect.moveBy(LayoutPoint(-paintContainer->localToAbsolute(FloatPoint())));
1292
1293 destinationRect = viewportRect;
1294 positioningAreaSize = destinationRect.size();
1295 positioningAreaSize.setHeight(positioningAreaSize.height() - topContentInset);
1296 positioningAreaSize = LayoutSize(snapRectToDevicePixels(LayoutRect(destinationRect.location(), positioningAreaSize), deviceScaleFactor).size());
1297 }
1298
1299 auto clientForBackgroundImage = backgroundObject ? backgroundObject : this;
1300 LayoutSize tileSize = calculateFillTileSize(fillLayer, positioningAreaSize);
1301 if (StyleImage* layerImage = fillLayer.image())
1302 layerImage->setContainerContextForRenderer(*clientForBackgroundImage, tileSize, style().effectiveZoom());
1303
1304 FillRepeat backgroundRepeatX = fillLayer.repeatX();
1305 FillRepeat backgroundRepeatY = fillLayer.repeatY();
1306 LayoutUnit availableWidth = positioningAreaSize.width() - tileSize.width();
1307 LayoutUnit availableHeight = positioningAreaSize.height() - tileSize.height();
1308
1309 LayoutSize spaceSize;
1310 LayoutSize phase;
1311 LayoutSize noRepeat;
1312 LayoutUnit computedXPosition = resolveEdgeRelativeLength(fillLayer.xPosition(), fillLayer.backgroundXOrigin(), availableWidth, positioningAreaSize, tileSize);
1313 if (backgroundRepeatX == FillRepeat::Round && positioningAreaSize.width() > 0 && tileSize.width() > 0) {
1314 int numTiles = std::max(1, roundToInt(positioningAreaSize.width() / tileSize.width()));
1315 if (fillLayer.size().size.height.isAuto() && backgroundRepeatY != FillRepeat::Round)
1316 tileSize.setHeight(tileSize.height() * positioningAreaSize.width() / (numTiles * tileSize.width()));
1317
1318 tileSize.setWidth(positioningAreaSize.width() / numTiles);
1319 phase.setWidth(tileSize.width() ? tileSize.width() - fmodf((computedXPosition + left), tileSize.width()) : 0);
1320 }
1321
1322 LayoutUnit computedYPosition = resolveEdgeRelativeLength(fillLayer.yPosition(), fillLayer.backgroundYOrigin(), availableHeight, positioningAreaSize, tileSize);
1323 if (backgroundRepeatY == FillRepeat::Round && positioningAreaSize.height() > 0 && tileSize.height() > 0) {
1324 int numTiles = std::max(1, roundToInt(positioningAreaSize.height() / tileSize.height()));
1325 if (fillLayer.size().size.width.isAuto() && backgroundRepeatX != FillRepeat::Round)
1326 tileSize.setWidth(tileSize.width() * positioningAreaSize.height() / (numTiles * tileSize.height()));
1327
1328 tileSize.setHeight(positioningAreaSize.height() / numTiles);
1329 phase.setHeight(tileSize.height() ? tileSize.height() - fmodf((computedYPosition + top), tileSize.height()) : 0);
1330 }
1331
1332 if (backgroundRepeatX == FillRepeat::Repeat) {
1333 phase.setWidth(tileSize.width() ? tileSize.width() - fmodf(computedXPosition + left, tileSize.width()) : 0);
1334 spaceSize.setWidth(0);
1335 } else if (backgroundRepeatX == FillRepeat::Space && tileSize.width() > 0) {
1336 LayoutUnit space = getSpace(positioningAreaSize.width(), tileSize.width());
1337 if (space >= 0) {
1338 LayoutUnit actualWidth = tileSize.width() + space;
1339 computedXPosition = minimumValueForLength(Length(), availableWidth);
1340 spaceSize.setWidth(space);
1341 spaceSize.setHeight(0);
1342 phase.setWidth(actualWidth ? actualWidth - fmodf((computedXPosition + left), actualWidth) : 0);
1343 } else
1344 backgroundRepeatX = FillRepeat::NoRepeat;
1345 }
1346
1347 if (backgroundRepeatX == FillRepeat::NoRepeat) {
1348 LayoutUnit xOffset = left + computedXPosition;
1349 if (xOffset > 0)
1350 destinationRect.move(xOffset, 0_lu);
1351 xOffset = std::min<LayoutUnit>(xOffset, 0);
1352 phase.setWidth(-xOffset);
1353 destinationRect.setWidth(tileSize.width() + xOffset);
1354 spaceSize.setWidth(0);
1355 }
1356
1357 if (backgroundRepeatY == FillRepeat::Repeat) {
1358 phase.setHeight(tileSize.height() ? tileSize.height() - fmodf(computedYPosition + top, tileSize.height()) : 0);
1359 spaceSize.setHeight(0);
1360 } else if (backgroundRepeatY == FillRepeat::Space && tileSize.height() > 0) {
1361 LayoutUnit space = getSpace(positioningAreaSize.height(), tileSize.height());
1362
1363 if (space >= 0) {
1364 LayoutUnit actualHeight = tileSize.height() + space;
1365 computedYPosition = minimumValueForLength(Length(), availableHeight);
1366 spaceSize.setHeight(space);
1367 phase.setHeight(actualHeight ? actualHeight - fmodf((computedYPosition + top), actualHeight) : 0);
1368 } else
1369 backgroundRepeatY = FillRepeat::NoRepeat;
1370 }
1371 if (backgroundRepeatY == FillRepeat::NoRepeat) {
1372 LayoutUnit yOffset = top + computedYPosition;
1373 if (yOffset > 0)
1374 destinationRect.move(0_lu, yOffset);
1375 yOffset = std::min<LayoutUnit>(yOffset, 0);
1376 phase.setHeight(-yOffset);
1377 destinationRect.setHeight(tileSize.height() + yOffset);
1378 spaceSize.setHeight(0);
1379 }
1380
1381 if (fixedAttachment) {
1382 LayoutPoint attachmentPoint = borderBoxRect.location();
1383 phase.expand(std::max<LayoutUnit>(attachmentPoint.x() - destinationRect.x(), 0), std::max<LayoutUnit>(attachmentPoint.y() - destinationRect.y(), 0));
1384 }
1385
1386 destinationRect.intersect(borderBoxRect);
1387 pixelSnapBackgroundImageGeometryForPainting(destinationRect, tileSize, phase, spaceSize, deviceScaleFactor);
1388 return BackgroundImageGeometry(destinationRect, tileSize, phase, spaceSize, fixedAttachment);
1389}
1390
1391void RenderBoxModelObject::getGeometryForBackgroundImage(const RenderLayerModelObject* paintContainer, const LayoutPoint& paintOffset, FloatRect& destRect, FloatSize& phase, FloatSize& tileSize) const
1392{
1393 LayoutRect paintRect(destRect);
1394 auto geometry = calculateBackgroundImageGeometry(paintContainer, style().backgroundLayers(), paintOffset, paintRect);
1395 phase = geometry.phase();
1396 tileSize = geometry.tileSize();
1397 destRect = geometry.destRect();
1398}

1400bool RenderBoxModelObject::paintNinePieceImage(GraphicsContext& graphicsContext, const LayoutRect& rect, const RenderStyle& style,
1401 const NinePieceImage& ninePieceImage, CompositeOperator op)
1402{
1403 StyleImage* styleImage = ninePieceImage.image();
1404 if (!styleImage)
1405 return false;
1406
1407 if (!styleImage->isLoaded())
1408 return true; // Never paint a nine-piece image incrementally, but don't paint the fallback borders either.
1409
1410 if (!styleImage->canRender(this, style.effectiveZoom()))
1411 return false;
1412
1413 // FIXME: border-image is broken with full page zooming when tiling has to happen, since the tiling function
1414 // doesn't have any understanding of the zoom that is in effect on the tile.
1415 float deviceScaleFactor = document().deviceScaleFactor();
1416
1417 LayoutRect rectWithOutsets = rect;
1418 rectWithOutsets.expand(style.imageOutsets(ninePieceImage));
1419 LayoutRect destination = LayoutRect(snapRectToDevicePixels(rectWithOutsets, deviceScaleFactor));
1420
1421 LayoutSize source = calculateImageIntrinsicDimensions(styleImage, destination.size(), DoNotScaleByEffectiveZoom);
1422
1423 // If both values are auto then the intrinsic width and/or height of the image should be used, if any.
1424 styleImage->setContainerContextForRenderer(*this, source, style.effectiveZoom());
1425
1426 ninePieceImage.paint(graphicsContext, this, style, destination, source, deviceScaleFactor, op);
1427 return true;
1428}
1429
1430static bool allCornersClippedOut(const RoundedRect& border, const LayoutRect& clipRect)
1431{
1432 LayoutRect boundingRect = border.rect();
1433 if (clipRect.contains(boundingRect))
1434 return false;
1435
1436 RoundedRect::Radii radii = border.radii();
1437
1438 LayoutRect topLeftRect(boundingRect.location(), radii.topLeft());
1439 if (clipRect.intersects(topLeftRect))
1440 return false;
1441
1442 LayoutRect topRightRect(boundingRect.location(), radii.topRight());
1443 topRightRect.setX(boundingRect.maxX() - topRightRect.width());
1444 if (clipRect.intersects(topRightRect))
1445 return false;
1446
1447 LayoutRect bottomLeftRect(boundingRect.location(), radii.bottomLeft());
1448 bottomLeftRect.setY(boundingRect.maxY() - bottomLeftRect.height());
1449 if (clipRect.intersects(bottomLeftRect))
1450 return false;
1451
1452 LayoutRect bottomRightRect(boundingRect.location(), radii.bottomRight());
1453 bottomRightRect.setX(boundingRect.maxX() - bottomRightRect.width());
1454 bottomRightRect.setY(boundingRect.maxY() - bottomRightRect.height());
1455 if (clipRect.intersects(bottomRightRect))
1456 return false;
1457
1458 return true;
1459}

1461static bool borderWillArcInnerEdge(const LayoutSize& firstRadius, const LayoutSize& secondRadius)
1462{
1463 return !firstRadius.isZero() || !secondRadius.isZero();
1464}
