1466inline bool styleRequiresClipPolygon(BorderStyle style)
1467{
1468 return style == BorderStyle::Dotted || style == BorderStyle::Dashed; // These are drawn with a stroke, so we have to clip to get corner miters.
1469}
1470
1471static bool borderStyleFillsBorderArea(BorderStyle style)
1472{
1473 return !(style == BorderStyle::Dotted || style == BorderStyle::Dashed || style == BorderStyle::Double);
1474}
1475
1476static bool borderStyleHasInnerDetail(BorderStyle style)
1477{
1478 return style == BorderStyle::Groove || style == BorderStyle::Ridge || style == BorderStyle::Double;
1479}
1480
1481static bool borderStyleIsDottedOrDashed(BorderStyle style)
1482{
1483 return style == BorderStyle::Dotted || style == BorderStyle::Dashed;
1484}
1485
1486// BorderStyle::Outset darkens the bottom and right (and maybe lightens the top and left)
1487// BorderStyle::Inset darkens the top and left (and maybe lightens the bottom and right)
1488static inline bool borderStyleHasUnmatchedColorsAtCorner(BorderStyle style, BoxSide side, BoxSide adjacentSide)
1489{
1490 // These styles match at the top/left and bottom/right.
1491 if (style == BorderStyle::Inset || style == BorderStyle::Groove || style == BorderStyle::Ridge || style == BorderStyle::Outset) {
1492 BoxSideSet topRightSides = { BoxSideFlag::Top, BoxSideFlag::Right };
1493 BoxSideSet bottomLeftSides = { BoxSideFlag::Bottom, BoxSideFlag::Left };
1494
1495 BoxSideSet usedSides { edgeFlagForSide(side), edgeFlagForSide(adjacentSide) };
1496 return usedSides == topRightSides || usedSides == bottomLeftSides;
1497 }
1498 return false;
1499}
1500
1501static inline bool colorsMatchAtCorner(BoxSide side, BoxSide adjacentSide, const BorderEdges& edges)
1502{
1503 auto& edge = edges.at(side);
1504 auto& adjacentEdge = edges.at(adjacentSide);
1505
1506 if (edge.shouldRender() != adjacentEdge.shouldRender())
1507 return false;
1508
1509 if (!edgesShareColor(edge, adjacentEdge))
1510 return false;
1511
1512 return !borderStyleHasUnmatchedColorsAtCorner(edge.style(), side, adjacentSide);
1513}
1514
1515
1516static inline bool colorNeedsAntiAliasAtCorner(BoxSide side, BoxSide adjacentSide, const BorderEdges& edges)
1517{
1518 auto& edge = edges.at(side);
1519 auto& adjacentEdge = edges.at(adjacentSide);
1520
1521 if (edge.color().isOpaque())
1522 return false;
1523
1524 if (edge.shouldRender() != adjacentEdge.shouldRender())
1525 return false;
1526
1527 if (!edgesShareColor(edge, adjacentEdge))
1528 return true;
1529
1530 return borderStyleHasUnmatchedColorsAtCorner(edge.style(), side, adjacentSide);
1531}
1532
1533// This assumes that we draw in order: top, bottom, left, right.
1534static inline bool willBeOverdrawn(BoxSide side, BoxSide adjacentSide, const BorderEdges& edges)
1535{
1536 switch (side) {
1537 case BoxSide::Top:
1538 case BoxSide::Bottom: {
1539 auto& edge = edges.at(side);
1540 auto& adjacentEdge = edges.at(adjacentSide);
1541
1542 if (adjacentEdge.presentButInvisible())
1543 return false;
1544
1545 if (!edgesShareColor(edge, adjacentEdge) && !adjacentEdge.color().isOpaque())
1546 return false;
1547
1548 if (!borderStyleFillsBorderArea(adjacentEdge.style()))
1549 return false;
1550
1551 return true;
1552 }
1553 case BoxSide::Left:
1554 case BoxSide::Right:
1555 // These draw last, so are never overdrawn.
1556 return false;
1557 }
1558 return false;
1559}
1560
1561static inline bool borderStylesRequireMitre(BoxSide side, BoxSide adjacentSide, BorderStyle style, BorderStyle adjacentStyle)
1562{
1563 if (style == BorderStyle::Double || adjacentStyle == BorderStyle::Double || adjacentStyle == BorderStyle::Groove || adjacentStyle == BorderStyle::Ridge)
1564 return true;
1565
1566 if (borderStyleIsDottedOrDashed(style) != borderStyleIsDottedOrDashed(adjacentStyle))
1567 return true;
1568
1569 if (style != adjacentStyle)
1570 return true;
1571
1572 return borderStyleHasUnmatchedColorsAtCorner(style, side, adjacentSide);
1573}
1574
1575static bool joinRequiresMitre(BoxSide side, BoxSide adjacentSide, const BorderEdges& edges, bool allowOverdraw)
1576{
1577 auto& edge = edges.at(side);
1578 auto& adjacentEdge = edges.at(adjacentSide);
1579
1580 if ((edge.isTransparent() && adjacentEdge.isTransparent()) || !adjacentEdge.isPresent())
1581 return false;
1582
1583 if (allowOverdraw && willBeOverdrawn(side, adjacentSide, edges))
1584 return false;
1585
1586 if (!edgesShareColor(edge, adjacentEdge))
1587 return true;
1588
1589 if (borderStylesRequireMitre(side, adjacentSide, edge.style(), adjacentEdge.style()))
1590 return true;
1591
1592 return false;
1593}
1594
1595static RoundedRect calculateAdjustedInnerBorder(const RoundedRect&innerBorder, BoxSide side)
1596{
1597 // Expand the inner border as necessary to make it a rounded rect (i.e. radii contained within each edge).
1598 // This function relies on the fact we only get radii not contained within each edge if one of the radii
1599 // for an edge is zero, so we can shift the arc towards the zero radius corner.
1600 RoundedRect::Radii newRadii = innerBorder.radii();
1601 LayoutRect newRect = innerBorder.rect();
1602
1603 float overshoot;
1604 float maxRadii;
1605
1606 switch (side) {
1607 case BoxSide::Top:
1608 overshoot = newRadii.topLeft().width() + newRadii.topRight().width() - newRect.width();
1609 if (overshoot > 0) {
1610 ASSERT(!(newRadii.topLeft().width() && newRadii.topRight().width()));
1611 newRect.setWidth(newRect.width() + overshoot);
1612 if (!newRadii.topLeft().width())
1613 newRect.move(-overshoot, 0);
1614 }
1615 newRadii.setBottomLeft({ });
1616 newRadii.setBottomRight({ });
1617 maxRadii = std::max(newRadii.topLeft().height(), newRadii.topRight().height());
1618 if (maxRadii > newRect.height())
1619 newRect.setHeight(maxRadii);
1620 break;
1621
1622 case BoxSide::Bottom:
1623 overshoot = newRadii.bottomLeft().width() + newRadii.bottomRight().width() - newRect.width();
1624 if (overshoot > 0) {
1625 ASSERT(!(newRadii.bottomLeft().width() && newRadii.bottomRight().width()));
1626 newRect.setWidth(newRect.width() + overshoot);
1627 if (!newRadii.bottomLeft().width())
1628 newRect.move(-overshoot, 0);
1629 }
1630 newRadii.setTopLeft({ });
1631 newRadii.setTopRight({ });
1632 maxRadii = std::max(newRadii.bottomLeft().height(), newRadii.bottomRight().height());
1633 if (maxRadii > newRect.height()) {
1634 newRect.move(0, newRect.height() - maxRadii);
1635 newRect.setHeight(maxRadii);
1636 }
1637 break;
1638
1639 case BoxSide::Left:
1640 overshoot = newRadii.topLeft().height() + newRadii.bottomLeft().height() - newRect.height();
1641 if (overshoot > 0) {
1642 ASSERT(!(newRadii.topLeft().height() && newRadii.bottomLeft().height()));
1643 newRect.setHeight(newRect.height() + overshoot);
1644 if (!newRadii.topLeft().height())
1645 newRect.move(0, -overshoot);
1646 }
1647 newRadii.setTopRight({ });
1648 newRadii.setBottomRight({ });
1649 maxRadii = std::max(newRadii.topLeft().width(), newRadii.bottomLeft().width());
1650 if (maxRadii > newRect.width())
1651 newRect.setWidth(maxRadii);
1652 break;
1653
1654 case BoxSide::Right:
1655 overshoot = newRadii.topRight().height() + newRadii.bottomRight().height() - newRect.height();
1656 if (overshoot > 0) {
1657 ASSERT(!(newRadii.topRight().height() && newRadii.bottomRight().height()));
1658 newRect.setHeight(newRect.height() + overshoot);
1659 if (!newRadii.topRight().height())
1660 newRect.move(0, -overshoot);
1661 }
1662 newRadii.setTopLeft({ });
1663 newRadii.setBottomLeft({ });
1664 maxRadii = std::max(newRadii.topRight().width(), newRadii.bottomRight().width());
1665 if (maxRadii > newRect.width()) {
1666 newRect.move(newRect.width() - maxRadii, 0);
1667 newRect.setWidth(maxRadii);
1668 }
1669 break;
1670 }
1671
1672 return RoundedRect(newRect, newRadii);
1673}
1674
1675void RenderBoxModelObject::paintOneBorderSide(GraphicsContext& graphicsContext, const RenderStyle& style, const RoundedRect& outerBorder, const RoundedRect& innerBorder,
1676 const LayoutRect& sideRect, BoxSide side, BoxSide adjacentSide1, BoxSide adjacentSide2, const BorderEdges& edges, const Path* path,
1677 BackgroundBleedAvoidance bleedAvoidance, bool includeLogicalLeftEdge, bool includeLogicalRightEdge, bool antialias, const Color* overrideColor)
1678{
1679 auto& edgeToRender = edges.at(side);
1680 ASSERT(edgeToRender.widthForPainting());
1681 auto& adjacentEdge1 = edges.at(adjacentSide1);
1682 auto& adjacentEdge2 = edges.at(adjacentSide2);
1683
1684 bool mitreAdjacentSide1 = joinRequiresMitre(side, adjacentSide1, edges, !antialias);
1685 bool mitreAdjacentSide2 = joinRequiresMitre(side, adjacentSide2, edges, !antialias);
1686
1687 bool adjacentSide1StylesMatch = colorsMatchAtCorner(side, adjacentSide1, edges);
1688 bool adjacentSide2StylesMatch = colorsMatchAtCorner(side, adjacentSide2, edges);
1689
1690 const Color& colorToPaint = overrideColor ? *overrideColor : edgeToRender.color();
1691
1692 if (path) {
1693 GraphicsContextStateSaver stateSaver(graphicsContext);
1694
1695 clipBorderSidePolygon(graphicsContext, outerBorder, innerBorder, side, adjacentSide1StylesMatch, adjacentSide2StylesMatch);
1696
1697 if (!innerBorder.isRenderable())
1698 graphicsContext.clipOutRoundedRect(FloatRoundedRect(calculateAdjustedInnerBorder(innerBorder, side)));
1699
1700 float thickness = std::max(std::max(edgeToRender.widthForPainting(), adjacentEdge1.widthForPainting()), adjacentEdge2.widthForPainting());
1701 drawBoxSideFromPath(graphicsContext, outerBorder.rect(), *path, edges, edgeToRender.widthForPainting(), thickness, side, style,
1702 colorToPaint, edgeToRender.style(), bleedAvoidance, includeLogicalLeftEdge, includeLogicalRightEdge);
1703 } else {
1704 bool clipForStyle = styleRequiresClipPolygon(edgeToRender.style()) && (mitreAdjacentSide1 || mitreAdjacentSide2);
1705 bool clipAdjacentSide1 = colorNeedsAntiAliasAtCorner(side, adjacentSide1, edges) && mitreAdjacentSide1;
1706 bool clipAdjacentSide2 = colorNeedsAntiAliasAtCorner(side, adjacentSide2, edges) && mitreAdjacentSide2;
1707 bool shouldClip = clipForStyle || clipAdjacentSide1 || clipAdjacentSide2;
1708
1709 GraphicsContextStateSaver clipStateSaver(graphicsContext, shouldClip);
1710 if (shouldClip) {
1711 bool aliasAdjacentSide1 = clipAdjacentSide1 || (clipForStyle && mitreAdjacentSide1);
1712 bool aliasAdjacentSide2 = clipAdjacentSide2 || (clipForStyle && mitreAdjacentSide2);
1713 clipBorderSidePolygon(graphicsContext, outerBorder, innerBorder, side, !aliasAdjacentSide1, !aliasAdjacentSide2);
1714 // Since we clipped, no need to draw with a mitre.
1715 mitreAdjacentSide1 = false;
1716 mitreAdjacentSide2 = false;
1717 }
1718 drawLineForBoxSide(graphicsContext, sideRect, side, colorToPaint, edgeToRender.style(), mitreAdjacentSide1 ? adjacentEdge1.widthForPainting() : 0, mitreAdjacentSide2 ? adjacentEdge2.widthForPainting() : 0, antialias);
1719 }
1720}
1721
1722static LayoutRect calculateSideRect(const RoundedRect& outerBorder, const BorderEdges& edges, BoxSide side)
1723{
1724 LayoutRect sideRect = outerBorder.rect();
1725 float width = edges.at(side).widthForPainting();
1726
1727 switch (side) {
1728 case BoxSide::Top:
1729 sideRect.setHeight(width);
1730 break;
1731 case BoxSide::Right:
1732 sideRect.shiftXEdgeTo(sideRect.maxX() - width);
1733 break;
1734 case BoxSide::Bottom:
1735 sideRect.shiftYEdgeTo(sideRect.maxY() - width);
1736 break;
1737 case BoxSide::Left:
1738 sideRect.setWidth(width);
1739 break;
1740 }
1741
1742 return sideRect;
1743}
1744
1745void RenderBoxModelObject::paintBorderSides(GraphicsContext& graphicsContext, const RenderStyle& style, const RoundedRect& outerBorder, const RoundedRect& innerBorder,
1746 const IntPoint& innerBorderAdjustment, const BorderEdges& edges, BoxSideSet edgeSet, BackgroundBleedAvoidance bleedAvoidance,
1747 bool includeLogicalLeftEdge, bool includeLogicalRightEdge, bool antialias, const Color* overrideColor)
1748{
1749 bool renderRadii = outerBorder.isRounded();
1750
1751 Path roundedPath;
1752 if (renderRadii)
1753 roundedPath.addRoundedRect(outerBorder);
1754
1755 // The inner border adjustment for bleed avoidance mode BackgroundBleedBackgroundOverBorder
1756 // is only applied to sideRect, which is okay since BackgroundBleedBackgroundOverBorder
1757 // is only to be used for solid borders and the shape of the border painted by drawBoxSideFromPath
1758 // only depends on sideRect when painting solid borders.
1759
1760 auto paintOneSide = [&](BoxSide side, BoxSide adjacentSide1, BoxSide adjacentSide2) {
1761 auto& edge = edges.at(side);
1762 if (!edge.shouldRender() || !edgeSet.contains(edgeFlagForSide(side)))
1763 return;
1764
1765 LayoutRect sideRect = outerBorder.rect();
1766 LayoutSize firstRadius;
1767 LayoutSize secondRadius;
1768
1769 switch (side) {
1770 case BoxSide::Top:
1771 sideRect.setHeight(edge.widthForPainting() + innerBorderAdjustment.y());
1772 firstRadius = innerBorder.radii().topLeft();
1773 secondRadius = innerBorder.radii().topRight();
1774 break;
1775 case BoxSide::Right:
1776 sideRect.shiftXEdgeTo(sideRect.maxX() - edge.widthForPainting() - innerBorderAdjustment.x());
1777 firstRadius = innerBorder.radii().bottomRight();
1778 secondRadius = innerBorder.radii().topRight();
1779 break;
1780 case BoxSide::Bottom:
1781 sideRect.shiftYEdgeTo(sideRect.maxY() - edge.widthForPainting() - innerBorderAdjustment.y());
1782 firstRadius = innerBorder.radii().bottomLeft();
1783 secondRadius = innerBorder.radii().bottomRight();
1784 break;
1785 case BoxSide::Left:
1786 sideRect.setWidth(edge.widthForPainting() + innerBorderAdjustment.x());
1787 firstRadius = innerBorder.radii().bottomLeft();
1788 secondRadius = innerBorder.radii().topLeft();
1789 break;
1790 }
1791
1792 bool usePath = renderRadii && (borderStyleHasInnerDetail(edge.style()) || borderWillArcInnerEdge(firstRadius, secondRadius));
1793 paintOneBorderSide(graphicsContext, style, outerBorder, innerBorder, sideRect, side, adjacentSide1, adjacentSide2, edges, usePath ? &roundedPath : nullptr, bleedAvoidance, includeLogicalLeftEdge, includeLogicalRightEdge, antialias, overrideColor);
1794 };
1795
1796 paintOneSide(BoxSide::Top, BoxSide::Left, BoxSide::Right);
1797 paintOneSide(BoxSide::Bottom, BoxSide::Left, BoxSide::Right);
1798 paintOneSide(BoxSide::Left, BoxSide::Top, BoxSide::Bottom);
1799 paintOneSide(BoxSide::Right, BoxSide::Top, BoxSide::Bottom);
1800}
1801
1802void RenderBoxModelObject::paintTranslucentBorderSides(GraphicsContext& graphicsContext, const RenderStyle& style, const RoundedRect& outerBorder, const RoundedRect& innerBorder, const IntPoint& innerBorderAdjustment,
1803 const BorderEdges& edges, BoxSideSet edgesToDraw, BackgroundBleedAvoidance bleedAvoidance, bool includeLogicalLeftEdge, bool includeLogicalRightEdge, bool antialias)
1804{
1805 // willBeOverdrawn assumes that we draw in order: top, bottom, left, right.
1806 // This is different from BoxSide enum order.
1807 static constexpr std::array<BoxSide, 4> paintOrderSides = { BoxSide::Top, BoxSide::Bottom, BoxSide::Left, BoxSide::Right };
1808
1809 while (edgesToDraw) {
1810 // Find undrawn edges sharing a color.
1811 Color commonColor;
1812
1813 BoxSideSet commonColorEdgeSet;
1814 for (auto side : paintOrderSides) {
1815 if (!edgesToDraw.contains(edgeFlagForSide(side)))
1816 continue;
1817
1818 auto& edge = edges.at(side);
1819 bool includeEdge;
1820 if (commonColorEdgeSet.isEmpty()) {
1821 commonColor = edge.color();
1822 includeEdge = true;
1823 } else
1824 includeEdge = edge.color() == commonColor;
1825
1826 if (includeEdge)
1827 commonColorEdgeSet.add(edgeFlagForSide(side));
1828 }
1829
1830 bool useTransparencyLayer = includesAdjacentEdges(commonColorEdgeSet) && !commonColor.isOpaque();
1831 if (useTransparencyLayer) {
1832 graphicsContext.beginTransparencyLayer(commonColor.alphaAsFloat());
1833 commonColor = commonColor.opaqueColor();
1834 }
1835
1836 paintBorderSides(graphicsContext, style, outerBorder, innerBorder, innerBorderAdjustment, edges, commonColorEdgeSet, bleedAvoidance, includeLogicalLeftEdge, includeLogicalRightEdge, antialias, &commonColor);
1837
1838 if (useTransparencyLayer)
1839 graphicsContext.endTransparencyLayer();
1840
1841 edgesToDraw.remove(commonColorEdgeSet);
1842 }
1843}
1844
1845void RenderBoxModelObject::paintBorder(const PaintInfo& info, const LayoutRect& rect, const RenderStyle& style,
1846 BackgroundBleedAvoidance bleedAvoidance, bool includeLogicalLeftEdge, bool includeLogicalRightEdge)
1847{
1848 GraphicsContext& graphicsContext = info.context();
1849
1850 if (graphicsContext.paintingDisabled())
1851 return;
1852
1853 if (rect.isEmpty())
1854 return;
1855
1856 auto rectToClipOut = paintRectToClipOutFromBorder(rect);
1857 bool appliedClipAlready = !rectToClipOut.isEmpty();
1858 GraphicsContextStateSaver stateSave(graphicsContext, appliedClipAlready);
1859 if (!rectToClipOut.isEmpty())
1860 graphicsContext.clipOut(snapRectToDevicePixels(rectToClipOut, document().deviceScaleFactor()));
1861
1862 // border-image is not affected by border-radius.
1863 if (paintNinePieceImage(graphicsContext, rect, style, style.borderImage()))
1864 return;
1865
1866 auto edges = borderEdges(style, document().deviceScaleFactor(), includeLogicalLeftEdge, includeLogicalRightEdge);
1867 RoundedRect outerBorder = style.getRoundedBorderFor(rect, includeLogicalLeftEdge, includeLogicalRightEdge);
1868 RoundedRect innerBorder = style.getRoundedInnerBorderFor(borderInnerRectAdjustedForBleedAvoidance(graphicsContext, rect, bleedAvoidance), includeLogicalLeftEdge, includeLogicalRightEdge);
1869
1870 // If no borders intersects with the dirty area, we can skip the border painting.
1871 if (innerBorder.contains(info.rect))
1872 return;
1873
1874 bool haveAlphaColor = false;
1875 bool haveAllSolidEdges = true;
1876 bool haveAllDoubleEdges = true;
1877 int numEdgesVisible = 4;
1878 bool allEdgesShareColor = true;
1879 std::optional<BoxSide> firstVisibleSide;
1880 BoxSideSet edgesToDraw;
1881
1882 for (auto side : allBoxSides) {
1883 auto& currEdge = edges.at(side);
1884
1885 if (currEdge.shouldRender())
1886 edgesToDraw.add(edgeFlagForSide(side));
1887
1888 if (currEdge.presentButInvisible()) {
1889 --numEdgesVisible;
1890 allEdgesShareColor = false;
1891 continue;
1892 }
1893
1894 if (!currEdge.widthForPainting()) {
1895 --numEdgesVisible;
1896 continue;
1897 }
1898
1899 if (!firstVisibleSide)
1900 firstVisibleSide = side;
1901 else if (currEdge.color() != edges.at(*firstVisibleSide).color())
1902 allEdgesShareColor = false;
1903
1904 if (!currEdge.color().isOpaque())
1905 haveAlphaColor = true;
1906
1907 if (currEdge.style() != BorderStyle::Solid)
1908 haveAllSolidEdges = false;
1909
1910 if (currEdge.style() != BorderStyle::Double)
1911 haveAllDoubleEdges = false;
1912 }
1913
1914 // If no corner intersects the clip region, we can pretend outerBorder is
1915 // rectangular to improve performance.
1916 if (haveAllSolidEdges && outerBorder.isRounded() && allCornersClippedOut(outerBorder, info.rect))
1917 outerBorder.setRadii(RoundedRect::Radii());
1918
1919 float deviceScaleFactor = document().deviceScaleFactor();
1920 // isRenderable() check avoids issue described in https://bugs.webkit.org/show_bug.cgi?id=38787
1921 if ((haveAllSolidEdges || haveAllDoubleEdges) && allEdgesShareColor && innerBorder.isRenderable()) {
1922 // Fast path for drawing all solid edges and all unrounded double edges
1923 if (numEdgesVisible == 4 && (outerBorder.isRounded() || haveAlphaColor)
1924 && (haveAllSolidEdges || (!outerBorder.isRounded() && !innerBorder.isRounded()))) {
1925 Path path;
1926
1927 FloatRoundedRect pixelSnappedOuterBorder = outerBorder.pixelSnappedRoundedRectForPainting(deviceScaleFactor);
1928 if (pixelSnappedOuterBorder.isRounded() && bleedAvoidance != BackgroundBleedUseTransparencyLayer)
1929 path.addRoundedRect(pixelSnappedOuterBorder);
1930 else
1931 path.addRect(pixelSnappedOuterBorder.rect());
1932
1933 if (haveAllDoubleEdges) {
1934 LayoutRect innerThirdRect = outerBorder.rect();
1935 LayoutRect outerThirdRect = outerBorder.rect();
1936 for (auto side : allBoxSides) {
1937 LayoutUnit outerWidth;
1938 LayoutUnit innerWidth;
1939 edges.at(side).getDoubleBorderStripeWidths(outerWidth, innerWidth);
1940 switch (side) {
1941 case BoxSide::Top:
1942 innerThirdRect.shiftYEdgeTo(innerThirdRect.y() + innerWidth);
1943 outerThirdRect.shiftYEdgeTo(outerThirdRect.y() + outerWidth);
1944 break;
1945 case BoxSide::Right:
1946 innerThirdRect.setWidth(innerThirdRect.width() - innerWidth);
1947 outerThirdRect.setWidth(outerThirdRect.width() - outerWidth);
1948 break;
1949 case BoxSide::Bottom:
1950 innerThirdRect.setHeight(innerThirdRect.height() - innerWidth);
1951 outerThirdRect.setHeight(outerThirdRect.height() - outerWidth);
1952 break;
1953 case BoxSide::Left:
1954 innerThirdRect.shiftXEdgeTo(innerThirdRect.x() + innerWidth);
1955 outerThirdRect.shiftXEdgeTo(outerThirdRect.x() + outerWidth);
1956 break;
1957 }
1958 }
1959
1960 FloatRoundedRect pixelSnappedOuterThird = outerBorder.pixelSnappedRoundedRectForPainting(deviceScaleFactor);
1961 pixelSnappedOuterThird.setRect(snapRectToDevicePixels(outerThirdRect, deviceScaleFactor));
1962
1963 if (pixelSnappedOuterThird.isRounded() && bleedAvoidance != BackgroundBleedUseTransparencyLayer)
1964 path.addRoundedRect(pixelSnappedOuterThird);
1965 else
1966 path.addRect(pixelSnappedOuterThird.rect());
1967
1968 FloatRoundedRect pixelSnappedInnerThird = innerBorder.pixelSnappedRoundedRectForPainting(deviceScaleFactor);
1969 pixelSnappedInnerThird.setRect(snapRectToDevicePixels(innerThirdRect, deviceScaleFactor));
1970 if (pixelSnappedInnerThird.isRounded() && bleedAvoidance != BackgroundBleedUseTransparencyLayer)
1971 path.addRoundedRect(pixelSnappedInnerThird);
1972 else
1973 path.addRect(pixelSnappedInnerThird.rect());
1974 }
1975
1976 FloatRoundedRect pixelSnappedInnerBorder = innerBorder.pixelSnappedRoundedRectForPainting(deviceScaleFactor);
1977 if (pixelSnappedInnerBorder.isRounded())
1978 path.addRoundedRect(pixelSnappedInnerBorder);
1979 else
1980 path.addRect(pixelSnappedInnerBorder.rect());
1981
1982 graphicsContext.setFillRule(WindRule::EvenOdd);
1983 graphicsContext.setFillColor(edges.at(*firstVisibleSide).color());
1984 graphicsContext.fillPath(path);
1985 return;
1986 }
1987 // Avoid creating transparent layers
1988 if (haveAllSolidEdges && numEdgesVisible != 4 && !outerBorder.isRounded() && haveAlphaColor) {
1989 Path path;
1990
1991 for (auto side : allBoxSides) {
1992 if (edges.at(side).shouldRender()) {
1993 auto sideRect = calculateSideRect(outerBorder, edges, side);
1994 path.addRect(sideRect); // FIXME: Need pixel snapping here.
1995 }
1996 }
1997
1998 graphicsContext.setFillRule(WindRule::NonZero);
1999 graphicsContext.setFillColor(edges.at(*firstVisibleSide).color());
2000 graphicsContext.fillPath(path);
2001 return;
2002 }
2003 }
2004
2005 bool clipToOuterBorder = outerBorder.isRounded();
2006 GraphicsContextStateSaver stateSaver(graphicsContext, clipToOuterBorder && !appliedClipAlready);
2007 if (clipToOuterBorder) {
2008 // Clip to the inner and outer radii rects.
2009 if (bleedAvoidance != BackgroundBleedUseTransparencyLayer)
2010 graphicsContext.clipRoundedRect(outerBorder.pixelSnappedRoundedRectForPainting(deviceScaleFactor));
2011 // isRenderable() check avoids issue described in https://bugs.webkit.org/show_bug.cgi?id=38787
2012 // The inside will be clipped out later (in clipBorderSideForComplexInnerPath)
2013 if (innerBorder.isRenderable())
2014 graphicsContext.clipOutRoundedRect(innerBorder.pixelSnappedRoundedRectForPainting(deviceScaleFactor));
2015 }
2016
2017 // If only one edge visible antialiasing doesn't create seams
2018 bool antialias = shouldAntialiasLines(graphicsContext) || numEdgesVisible == 1;
2019 RoundedRect unadjustedInnerBorder = (bleedAvoidance == BackgroundBleedBackgroundOverBorder) ? style.getRoundedInnerBorderFor(rect, includeLogicalLeftEdge, includeLogicalRightEdge) : innerBorder;
2020 IntPoint innerBorderAdjustment(innerBorder.rect().x() - unadjustedInnerBorder.rect().x(), innerBorder.rect().y() - unadjustedInnerBorder.rect().y());
2021 if (haveAlphaColor)
2022 paintTranslucentBorderSides(graphicsContext, style, outerBorder, unadjustedInnerBorder, innerBorderAdjustment, edges, edgesToDraw, bleedAvoidance, includeLogicalLeftEdge, includeLogicalRightEdge, antialias);
2023 else
2024 paintBorderSides(graphicsContext, style, outerBorder, unadjustedInnerBorder, innerBorderAdjustment, edges, edgesToDraw, bleedAvoidance, includeLogicalLeftEdge, includeLogicalRightEdge, antialias);
2025}
2026
2027void RenderBoxModelObject::drawBoxSideFromPath(GraphicsContext& graphicsContext, const LayoutRect& borderRect, const Path& borderPath, const BorderEdges& edges,
2028 float thickness, float drawThickness, BoxSide side, const RenderStyle& style, Color color, BorderStyle borderStyle, BackgroundBleedAvoidance bleedAvoidance,
2029 bool includeLogicalLeftEdge, bool includeLogicalRightEdge)
2030{
2031 if (thickness <= 0)
2032 return;
2033
2034 if (borderStyle == BorderStyle::Double && thickness < 3)
2035 borderStyle = BorderStyle::Solid;
2036
2037 switch (borderStyle) {
2038 case BorderStyle::None:
2039 case BorderStyle::Hidden:
2040 return;
2041 case BorderStyle::Dotted:
2042 case BorderStyle::Dashed: {
2043 graphicsContext.setStrokeColor(color);
2044
2045 // The stroke is doubled here because the provided path is the
2046 // outside edge of the border so half the stroke is clipped off.
2047 // The extra multiplier is so that the clipping mask can antialias
2048 // the edges to prevent jaggies.
2049 graphicsContext.setStrokeThickness(drawThickness * 2 * 1.1f);
2050 graphicsContext.setStrokeStyle(borderStyle == BorderStyle::Dashed ? DashedStroke : DottedStroke);
2051
2052 // If the number of dashes that fit in the path is odd and non-integral then we
2053 // will have an awkwardly-sized dash at the end of the path. To try to avoid that
2054 // here, we simply make the whitespace dashes ever so slightly bigger.
2055 // FIXME: This could be even better if we tried to manipulate the dash offset
2056 // and possibly the gapLength to get the corners dash-symmetrical.
2057 float dashLength = thickness * ((borderStyle == BorderStyle::Dashed) ? 3.0f : 1.0f);
2058 float gapLength = dashLength;
2059 float numberOfDashes = borderPath.length() / dashLength;
2060 // Don't try to show dashes if we have less than 2 dashes + 2 gaps.
2061 // FIXME: should do this test per side.
2062 if (numberOfDashes >= 4) {
2063 bool evenNumberOfFullDashes = !((int)numberOfDashes % 2);
2064 bool integralNumberOfDashes = !(numberOfDashes - (int)numberOfDashes);
2065 if (!evenNumberOfFullDashes && !integralNumberOfDashes) {
2066 float numberOfGaps = numberOfDashes / 2;
2067 gapLength += (dashLength / numberOfGaps);
2068 }
2069
2070 DashArray lineDash;
2071 lineDash.append(dashLength);
2072 lineDash.append(gapLength);
2073 graphicsContext.setLineDash(lineDash, dashLength);
2074 }
2075
2076 // FIXME: stroking the border path causes issues with tight corners:
2077 // https://bugs.webkit.org/show_bug.cgi?id=58711
2078 // Also, to get the best appearance we should stroke a path between the two borders.
2079 graphicsContext.strokePath(borderPath);
2080 return;
2081 }
2082 case BorderStyle::Double: {
2083 // Get the inner border rects for both the outer border line and the inner border line
2084 LayoutUnit outerBorderTopWidth;
2085 LayoutUnit innerBorderTopWidth;
2086 edges.top().getDoubleBorderStripeWidths(outerBorderTopWidth, innerBorderTopWidth);
2087
2088 LayoutUnit outerBorderRightWidth;
2089 LayoutUnit innerBorderRightWidth;
2090 edges.right().getDoubleBorderStripeWidths(outerBorderRightWidth, innerBorderRightWidth);
2091
2092 LayoutUnit outerBorderBottomWidth;
2093 LayoutUnit innerBorderBottomWidth;
2094 edges.bottom().getDoubleBorderStripeWidths(outerBorderBottomWidth, innerBorderBottomWidth);
2095
2096 LayoutUnit outerBorderLeftWidth;
2097 LayoutUnit innerBorderLeftWidth;
2098 edges.left().getDoubleBorderStripeWidths(outerBorderLeftWidth, innerBorderLeftWidth);
2099
2100 // Draw inner border line
2101 {
2102 GraphicsContextStateSaver stateSaver(graphicsContext);
2103 RoundedRect innerClip = style.getRoundedInnerBorderFor(borderRect,
2104 innerBorderTopWidth, innerBorderBottomWidth, innerBorderLeftWidth, innerBorderRightWidth,
2105 includeLogicalLeftEdge, includeLogicalRightEdge);
2106
2107 graphicsContext.clipRoundedRect(FloatRoundedRect(innerClip));
2108 drawBoxSideFromPath(graphicsContext, borderRect, borderPath, edges, thickness, drawThickness, side, style, color, BorderStyle::Solid, bleedAvoidance, includeLogicalLeftEdge, includeLogicalRightEdge);
2109 }
2110
2111 // Draw outer border line
2112 {
2113 GraphicsContextStateSaver stateSaver(graphicsContext);
2114 LayoutRect outerRect = borderRect;
2115 if (bleedAvoidance == BackgroundBleedUseTransparencyLayer) {
2116 outerRect.inflate(1);
2117 ++outerBorderTopWidth;
2118 ++outerBorderBottomWidth;
2119 ++outerBorderLeftWidth;
2120 ++outerBorderRightWidth;
2121 }
2122
2123 RoundedRect outerClip = style.getRoundedInnerBorderFor(outerRect,
2124 outerBorderTopWidth, outerBorderBottomWidth, outerBorderLeftWidth, outerBorderRightWidth,
2125 includeLogicalLeftEdge, includeLogicalRightEdge);
2126 graphicsContext.clipOutRoundedRect(FloatRoundedRect(outerClip));
2127 drawBoxSideFromPath(graphicsContext, borderRect, borderPath, edges, thickness, drawThickness, side, style, color, BorderStyle::Solid, bleedAvoidance, includeLogicalLeftEdge, includeLogicalRightEdge);
2128 }
2129 return;
2130 }
2131 case BorderStyle::Ridge:
2132 case BorderStyle::Groove:
2133 {
2134 BorderStyle s1;
2135 BorderStyle s2;
2136 if (borderStyle == BorderStyle::Groove) {
2137 s1 = BorderStyle::Inset;
2138 s2 = BorderStyle::Outset;
2139 } else {
2140 s1 = BorderStyle::Outset;
2141 s2 = BorderStyle::Inset;
2142 }
2143
2144 // Paint full border
2145 drawBoxSideFromPath(graphicsContext, borderRect, borderPath, edges, thickness, drawThickness, side, style, color, s1, bleedAvoidance, includeLogicalLeftEdge, includeLogicalRightEdge);
2146
2147 // Paint inner only
2148 GraphicsContextStateSaver stateSaver(graphicsContext);
2149 LayoutUnit topWidth { edges.top().widthForPainting() / 2 };
2150 LayoutUnit bottomWidth { edges.bottom().widthForPainting() / 2 };
2151 LayoutUnit leftWidth { edges.left().widthForPainting() / 2 };
2152 LayoutUnit rightWidth { edges.right().widthForPainting() / 2 };
2153
2154 RoundedRect clipRect = style.getRoundedInnerBorderFor(borderRect,
2155 topWidth, bottomWidth, leftWidth, rightWidth,
2156 includeLogicalLeftEdge, includeLogicalRightEdge);
2157
2158 graphicsContext.clipRoundedRect(FloatRoundedRect(clipRect));
2159 drawBoxSideFromPath(graphicsContext, borderRect, borderPath, edges, thickness, drawThickness, side, style, color, s2, bleedAvoidance, includeLogicalLeftEdge, includeLogicalRightEdge);
2160 return;
2161 }
2162 case BorderStyle::Inset:
2163 case BorderStyle::Outset:
2164 calculateBorderStyleColor(borderStyle, side, color);
2165 break;
2166 default:
2167 break;
2168 }
2169
2170 graphicsContext.setStrokeStyle(NoStroke);
2171 graphicsContext.setFillColor(color);
2172 graphicsContext.drawRect(snapRectToDevicePixels(borderRect, document().deviceScaleFactor()));
2173}
2174
2175void RenderBoxModelObject::clipBorderSidePolygon(GraphicsContext& graphicsContext, const RoundedRect& outerBorder, const RoundedRect& innerBorder,
2176 BoxSide side, bool firstEdgeMatches, bool secondEdgeMatches)
2177{
2178 float deviceScaleFactor = document().deviceScaleFactor();
2179 const FloatRect& outerRect = snapRectToDevicePixels(outerBorder.rect(), deviceScaleFactor);
2180 const FloatRect& innerRect = snapRectToDevicePixels(innerBorder.rect(), deviceScaleFactor);
2181
2182 // For each side, create a quad that encompasses all parts of that side that may draw,
2183 // including areas inside the innerBorder.
2184 //
2185 // 0----------------3
2186 // 0 \ / 0
2187 // |\ 1----------- 2 /|
2188 // | 1 1 |
2189 // | | | |
2190 // | | | |
2191 // | 2 2 |
2192 // |/ 1------------2 \|
2193 // 3 / \ 3
2194 // 0----------------3
2195 //
2196 Vector<FloatPoint> quad;
2197 quad.reserveInitialCapacity(4);
2198 switch (side) {
2199 case BoxSide::Top:
2200 quad.uncheckedAppend(outerRect.minXMinYCorner());
2201 quad.uncheckedAppend(innerRect.minXMinYCorner());
2202 quad.uncheckedAppend(innerRect.maxXMinYCorner());
2203 quad.uncheckedAppend(outerRect.maxXMinYCorner());
2204
2205 if (!innerBorder.radii().topLeft().isZero())
2206 findIntersection(outerRect.minXMinYCorner(), innerRect.minXMinYCorner(), innerRect.minXMaxYCorner(), innerRect.maxXMinYCorner(), quad[1]);
2207
2208 if (!innerBorder.radii().topRight().isZero())
2209 findIntersection(outerRect.maxXMinYCorner(), innerRect.maxXMinYCorner(), innerRect.minXMinYCorner(), innerRect.maxXMaxYCorner(), quad[2]);
2210 break;
2211
2212 case BoxSide::Left:
2213 quad.uncheckedAppend(outerRect.minXMinYCorner());
2214 quad.uncheckedAppend(innerRect.minXMinYCorner());
2215 quad.uncheckedAppend(innerRect.minXMaxYCorner());
2216 quad.uncheckedAppend(outerRect.minXMaxYCorner());
2217
2218 if (!innerBorder.radii().topLeft().isZero())
2219 findIntersection(outerRect.minXMinYCorner(), innerRect.minXMinYCorner(), innerRect.minXMaxYCorner(), innerRect.maxXMinYCorner(), quad[1]);
2220
2221 if (!innerBorder.radii().bottomLeft().isZero())
2222 findIntersection(outerRect.minXMaxYCorner(), innerRect.minXMaxYCorner(), innerRect.minXMinYCorner(), innerRect.maxXMaxYCorner(), quad[2]);
2223 break;
2224
2225 case BoxSide::Bottom:
2226 quad.uncheckedAppend(outerRect.minXMaxYCorner());
2227 quad.uncheckedAppend(innerRect.minXMaxYCorner());
2228 quad.uncheckedAppend(innerRect.maxXMaxYCorner());
2229 quad.uncheckedAppend(outerRect.maxXMaxYCorner());
2230
2231 if (!innerBorder.radii().bottomLeft().isZero())
2232 findIntersection(outerRect.minXMaxYCorner(), innerRect.minXMaxYCorner(), innerRect.minXMinYCorner(), innerRect.maxXMaxYCorner(), quad[1]);
2233
2234 if (!innerBorder.radii().bottomRight().isZero())
2235 findIntersection(outerRect.maxXMaxYCorner(), innerRect.maxXMaxYCorner(), innerRect.maxXMinYCorner(), innerRect.minXMaxYCorner(), quad[2]);
2236 break;
2237
2238 case BoxSide::Right:
2239 quad.uncheckedAppend(outerRect.maxXMinYCorner());
2240 quad.uncheckedAppend(innerRect.maxXMinYCorner());
2241 quad.uncheckedAppend(innerRect.maxXMaxYCorner());
2242 quad.uncheckedAppend(outerRect.maxXMaxYCorner());
2243
2244 if (!innerBorder.radii().topRight().isZero())
2245 findIntersection(outerRect.maxXMinYCorner(), innerRect.maxXMinYCorner(), innerRect.minXMinYCorner(), innerRect.maxXMaxYCorner(), quad[1]);
2246
2247 if (!innerBorder.radii().bottomRight().isZero())
2248 findIntersection(outerRect.maxXMaxYCorner(), innerRect.maxXMaxYCorner(), innerRect.maxXMinYCorner(), innerRect.minXMaxYCorner(), quad[2]);
2249 break;
2250 }
2251
2252 // If the border matches both of its adjacent sides, don't anti-alias the clip, and
2253 // if neither side matches, anti-alias the clip.
2254 if (firstEdgeMatches == secondEdgeMatches) {
2255 bool wasAntialiased = graphicsContext.shouldAntialias();
2256 graphicsContext.setShouldAntialias(!firstEdgeMatches);
2257 graphicsContext.clipPath(Path::polygonPathFromPoints(quad), WindRule::NonZero);
2258 graphicsContext.setShouldAntialias(wasAntialiased);
2259 return;
2260 }
2261
2262 // Square off the end which shouldn't be affected by antialiasing, and clip.
2263 Vector<FloatPoint> firstQuad = {
2264 quad[0],
2265 quad[1],
2266 quad[2],
2267 side == BoxSide::Top || side == BoxSide::Bottom ? FloatPoint(quad[3].x(), quad[2].y()) : FloatPoint(quad[2].x(), quad[3].y()),
2268 quad[3]
2269 };
2270 bool wasAntialiased = graphicsContext.shouldAntialias();
2271 graphicsContext.setShouldAntialias(!firstEdgeMatches);
2272 graphicsContext.clipPath(Path::polygonPathFromPoints(firstQuad), WindRule::NonZero);
2273
2274 Vector<FloatPoint> secondQuad = {
2275 quad[0],
2276 side == BoxSide::Top || side == BoxSide::Bottom ? FloatPoint(quad[0].x(), quad[1].y()) : FloatPoint(quad[1].x(), quad[0].y()),
2277 quad[1],
2278 quad[2],
2279 quad[3]
2280 };
2281 // Antialiasing affects the second side.
2282 graphicsContext.setShouldAntialias(!secondEdgeMatches);
2283 graphicsContext.clipPath(Path::polygonPathFromPoints(secondQuad), WindRule::NonZero);
2284
2285 graphicsContext.setShouldAntialias(wasAntialiased);
2286}

2322bool RenderBoxModelObject::boxShadowShouldBeAppliedToBackground(const LayoutPoint&, BackgroundBleedAvoidance bleedAvoidance, LegacyInlineFlowBox* inlineFlowBox) const
2323{
2324 if (bleedAvoidance != BackgroundBleedNone)
2325 return false;
2326
2327 if (style().hasAppearance())
2328 return false;
2329
2330 bool hasOneNormalBoxShadow = false;
2331 for (const ShadowData* currentShadow = style().boxShadow(); currentShadow; currentShadow = currentShadow->next()) {
2332 if (currentShadow->style() != ShadowStyle::Normal)
2333 continue;
2334
2335 if (hasOneNormalBoxShadow)
2336 return false;
2337 hasOneNormalBoxShadow = true;
2338
2339 if (currentShadow->spread())
2340 return false;
2341 }
2342
2343 if (!hasOneNormalBoxShadow)
2344 return false;
2345
2346 Color backgroundColor = style().visitedDependentColorWithColorFilter(CSSPropertyBackgroundColor);
2347 if (!backgroundColor.isOpaque())
2348 return false;
2349
2350 auto* lastBackgroundLayer = &style().backgroundLayers();
2351 while (auto* next = lastBackgroundLayer->next())
2352 lastBackgroundLayer = next;
2353
2354 if (lastBackgroundLayer->clip() != FillBox::Border)
2355 return false;
2356
2357 if (lastBackgroundLayer->image() && style().hasBorderRadius())
2358 return false;
2359
2360 if (inlineFlowBox && !inlineFlowBox->boxShadowCanBeAppliedToBackground(*lastBackgroundLayer))
2361 return false;
2362
2363 if (hasOverflowClip() && lastBackgroundLayer->attachment() == FillAttachment::LocalBackground)
2364 return false;
2365
2366 return true;
2367}

2369static inline LayoutRect areaCastingShadowInHole(const LayoutRect& holeRect, LayoutUnit shadowExtent, LayoutUnit shadowSpread, const LayoutSize& shadowOffset)

2372
2373 bounds.inflate(shadowExtent);
2374
2375 if (shadowSpread < 0)
2376 bounds.inflate(-shadowSpread);
2377
2378 LayoutRect offsetBounds = bounds;
2379 offsetBounds.move(-shadowOffset);
2380 return unionRect(bounds, offsetBounds);

2383void RenderBoxModelObject::paintBoxShadow(const PaintInfo& info, const LayoutRect& paintRect, const RenderStyle& style, ShadowStyle shadowStyle, bool includeLogicalLeftEdge, bool includeLogicalRightEdge)
2384{
2385 // FIXME: Deal with border-image. Would be great to use border-image as a mask.
2386 GraphicsContext& context = info.context();
2387 if (context.paintingDisabled() || !style.boxShadow())
2388 return;
2389
2390 RoundedRect borderRect = (shadowStyle == ShadowStyle::Inset) ? style.getRoundedInnerBorderFor(paintRect, includeLogicalLeftEdge, includeLogicalRightEdge)
2391 : style.getRoundedBorderFor(paintRect, includeLogicalLeftEdge, includeLogicalRightEdge);
2392
2393 bool hasBorderRadius = style.hasBorderRadius();
2394 float deviceScaleFactor = document().deviceScaleFactor();
2395
2396 bool hasOpaqueBackground = style.visitedDependentColorWithColorFilter(CSSPropertyBackgroundColor).isOpaque();
2397 for (const ShadowData* shadow = style.boxShadow(); shadow; shadow = shadow->next()) {
2398 if (shadow->style() != shadowStyle)
2399 continue;
2400
2401 LayoutSize shadowOffset(shadow->x(), shadow->y());
2402 LayoutUnit shadowPaintingExtent = shadow->paintingExtent();
2403 LayoutUnit shadowSpread = shadow->spread();
2404 int shadowRadius = shadow->radius();
2405
2406 if (shadowOffset.isZero() && !shadowRadius && !shadowSpread)
2407 continue;
2408
2409 Color shadowColor = style.colorByApplyingColorFilter(shadow->color());
2410
2411 if (shadow->style() == ShadowStyle::Normal) {
2412 auto fillRect = borderRect;
2413 fillRect.inflate(shadowSpread);
2414 if (fillRect.isEmpty())
2415 continue;
2416
2417 auto shadowRect = borderRect.rect();
2418 shadowRect.inflate(shadowPaintingExtent + shadowSpread);
2419 shadowRect.move(shadowOffset);
2420 auto pixelSnappedShadowRect = snapRectToDevicePixels(shadowRect, deviceScaleFactor);
2421
2422 GraphicsContextStateSaver stateSaver(context);
2423 context.clip(pixelSnappedShadowRect);
2424
2425 // Move the fill just outside the clip, adding at least 1 pixel of separation so that the fill does not
2426 // bleed in (due to antialiasing) if the context is transformed.
2427 LayoutUnit xOffset = paintRect.width() + std::max<LayoutUnit>(0, shadowOffset.width()) + shadowPaintingExtent + 2 * shadowSpread + LayoutUnit(1);
2428 LayoutSize extraOffset(xOffset.ceil(), 0);
2429 shadowOffset -= extraOffset;
2430 fillRect.move(extraOffset);
2431
2432 auto pixelSnappedRectToClipOut = borderRect.pixelSnappedRoundedRectForPainting(deviceScaleFactor);
2433 auto pixelSnappedFillRect = fillRect.pixelSnappedRoundedRectForPainting(deviceScaleFactor);
2434
2435 LayoutPoint shadowRectOrigin = fillRect.rect().location() + shadowOffset;
2436 FloatPoint snappedShadowOrigin = FloatPoint(roundToDevicePixel(shadowRectOrigin.x(), deviceScaleFactor), roundToDevicePixel(shadowRectOrigin.y(), deviceScaleFactor));
2437 FloatSize snappedShadowOffset = snappedShadowOrigin - pixelSnappedFillRect.rect().location();
2438
2439 context.setShadow(snappedShadowOffset, shadowRadius, shadowColor, shadow->isWebkitBoxShadow() ? ShadowRadiusMode::Legacy : ShadowRadiusMode::Default);
2440
2441 if (hasBorderRadius) {
2442 // If the box is opaque, it is unnecessary to clip it out. However, doing so saves time
2443 // when painting the shadow. On the other hand, it introduces subpixel gaps along the
2444 // corners. Those are avoided by insetting the clipping path by one pixel.
2445 if (hasOpaqueBackground)
2446 pixelSnappedRectToClipOut.inflateWithRadii(-1.0f);
2447
2448 if (!pixelSnappedRectToClipOut.isEmpty())
2449 context.clipOutRoundedRect(pixelSnappedRectToClipOut);
2450
2451 RoundedRect influenceRect(LayoutRect(pixelSnappedShadowRect), borderRect.radii());
2452 influenceRect.expandRadii(2 * shadowPaintingExtent + shadowSpread);
2453
2454 if (allCornersClippedOut(influenceRect, info.rect))
2455 context.fillRect(pixelSnappedFillRect.rect(), Color::black);
2456 else {
2457 pixelSnappedFillRect.expandRadii(shadowSpread);
2458 if (!pixelSnappedFillRect.isRenderable())
2459 pixelSnappedFillRect.adjustRadii();
2460 context.fillRoundedRect(pixelSnappedFillRect, Color::black);
2461 }
2462 } else {
2463 // If the box is opaque, it is unnecessary to clip it out. However, doing so saves time
2464 // when painting the shadow. On the other hand, it introduces subpixel gaps along the
2465 // edges if they are not pixel-aligned. Those are avoided by insetting the clipping path
2466 // by one pixel.
2467 if (hasOpaqueBackground) {
2468 // FIXME: The function to decide on the policy based on the transform should be a named function.
2469 // FIXME: It's not clear if this check is right. What about integral scale factors?
2470 AffineTransform transform = context.getCTM();
2471 if (transform.a() != 1 || (transform.d() != 1 && transform.d() != -1) || transform.b() || transform.c())
2472 pixelSnappedRectToClipOut.inflate(-1.0f);
2473 }
2474
2475 if (!pixelSnappedRectToClipOut.isEmpty())
2476 context.clipOut(pixelSnappedRectToClipOut.rect());
2477
2478 context.fillRect(pixelSnappedFillRect.rect(), Color::black);
2479 }
2480 } else {
2481 // Inset shadow.
2482 auto holeRect = borderRect.rect();
2483 holeRect.inflate(-shadowSpread);
2484
2485 bool isHorizontal = style.isHorizontalWritingMode();
2486 if (!includeLogicalLeftEdge) {
2487 if (isHorizontal)
2488 holeRect.shiftXEdgeBy(-(std::max<LayoutUnit>(shadowOffset.width(), 0) + shadowPaintingExtent + shadowSpread));
2489 else
2490 holeRect.shiftYEdgeBy(-(std::max<LayoutUnit>(shadowOffset.height(), 0) + shadowPaintingExtent + shadowSpread));
2491 }
2492
2493 if (!includeLogicalRightEdge) {
2494 if (isHorizontal)
2495 holeRect.setWidth(holeRect.width() - std::min<LayoutUnit>(shadowOffset.width(), 0) + shadowPaintingExtent + shadowSpread);
2496 else
2497 holeRect.setHeight(holeRect.height() - std::min<LayoutUnit>(shadowOffset.height(), 0) + shadowPaintingExtent + shadowSpread);
2498 }
2499
2500 auto roundedHoleRect = RoundedRect { holeRect, borderRect.radii() };
2501 if (shadowSpread && roundedHoleRect.isRounded()) {
2502 auto rounedRectCorrectingForSpread = [&]() {
2503 bool horizontal = style.isHorizontalWritingMode();
2504 LayoutUnit leftWidth { (!horizontal || includeLogicalLeftEdge) ? style.borderLeftWidth() + shadowSpread : 0 };
2505 LayoutUnit rightWidth { (!horizontal || includeLogicalRightEdge) ? style.borderRightWidth() + shadowSpread : 0 };
2506 LayoutUnit topWidth { (horizontal || includeLogicalLeftEdge) ? style.borderTopWidth() + shadowSpread : 0 };
2507 LayoutUnit bottomWidth { (horizontal || includeLogicalRightEdge) ? style.borderBottomWidth() + shadowSpread : 0 };
2508
2509 return style.getRoundedInnerBorderFor(paintRect, topWidth, bottomWidth, leftWidth, rightWidth, includeLogicalLeftEdge, includeLogicalRightEdge);
2510 }();
2511 roundedHoleRect.setRadii(rounedRectCorrectingForSpread.radii());
2512 }
2513
2514 auto pixelSnappedHoleRect = roundedHoleRect.pixelSnappedRoundedRectForPainting(deviceScaleFactor);
2515 auto pixelSnappedBorderRect = borderRect.pixelSnappedRoundedRectForPainting(deviceScaleFactor);
2516 if (pixelSnappedHoleRect.isEmpty()) {
2517 if (hasBorderRadius)
2518 context.fillRoundedRect(pixelSnappedBorderRect, shadowColor);
2519 else
2520 context.fillRect(pixelSnappedBorderRect.rect(), shadowColor);
2521 continue;
2522 }
2523
2524 Color fillColor = shadowColor.opaqueColor();
2525 auto shadowCastingRect = areaCastingShadowInHole(borderRect.rect(), shadowPaintingExtent, shadowSpread, shadowOffset);
2526 auto pixelSnappedOuterRect = snapRectToDevicePixels(shadowCastingRect, deviceScaleFactor);
2527
2528 GraphicsContextStateSaver stateSaver(context);
2529 if (hasBorderRadius)
2530 context.clipRoundedRect(pixelSnappedBorderRect);
2531 else
2532 context.clip(pixelSnappedBorderRect.rect());
2533
2534 LayoutUnit xOffset = 2 * paintRect.width() + std::max<LayoutUnit>(0, shadowOffset.width()) + shadowPaintingExtent - 2 * shadowSpread + LayoutUnit(1);
2535 LayoutSize extraOffset(xOffset.ceil(), 0);
2536
2537 context.translate(extraOffset);
2538 shadowOffset -= extraOffset;
2539
2540 context.setShadow(shadowOffset, shadowRadius, shadowColor, shadow->isWebkitBoxShadow() ? ShadowRadiusMode::Legacy : ShadowRadiusMode::Default);
2541 context.fillRectWithRoundedHole(pixelSnappedOuterRect, pixelSnappedHoleRect, fillColor);
2542 }
2543 }
2544}

2660void RenderBoxModelObject::collectAbsoluteQuadsForContinuation(Vector<FloatQuad>& quads, bool* wasFixed) const
2661{
2662 ASSERT(continuation());
2663 for (auto* nextInContinuation = this->continuation(); nextInContinuation; nextInContinuation = nextInContinuation->continuation()) {
2664 if (is<RenderBlock>(*nextInContinuation)) {
2665 auto& blockBox = downcast<RenderBlock>(*nextInContinuation);
2666 // For blocks inside inlines, we include margins so that we run right up to the inline boxes
2667 // above and below us (thus getting merged with them to form a single irregular shape).
2668 auto logicalRect = FloatRect { 0, -blockBox.collapsedMarginBefore(), blockBox.width(),
2669 blockBox.height() + blockBox.collapsedMarginBefore() + blockBox.collapsedMarginAfter() };
2670 nextInContinuation->absoluteQuadsIgnoringContinuation(logicalRect, quads, wasFixed);
2671 continue;
2672 }
2673 nextInContinuation->absoluteQuadsIgnoringContinuation({ }, quads, wasFixed);
2674 }
